WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:01:03.939 --> 00:01:05.566
(Wildlife squawking)

3
00:01:06.233 --> 00:01:07.859
(Man panting)

4
00:01:10.821 --> 00:01:13.240
(Natives yelling)

5
00:01:16.577 --> 00:01:18.078
(Yelling continues)

6
00:01:26.920 --> 00:01:29.006
({screams) {Screeches)

7
00:01:33.510 --> 00:01:36.179
Damn it. man! That was our
ride! You just stunned our ride!

8
00:01:38.181 --> 00:01:39.182
On. great.

9
00:01:39.266 --> 00:01:40.267
(Native yells)

10
00:01:40.517 --> 00:01:41.518
Run!

11
00:01:41.602 --> 00:01:43.312
(Natives ululating)

12
00:01:45.522 --> 00:01:47.024
(Speaking local language)

13
00:01:47.858 --> 00:01:49.318
What the hell did you take?

14
00:01:49.359 --> 00:01:51.236
I have no idea.
but they were bowing to it.

15
00:01:52.029 --> 00:01:53.196
Kirk to shuttle one.

16
00:01:53.572 --> 00:01:54.990
Locals are out of the kill zone.

17
00:01:55.032 --> 00:01:56.325
You are clear. Repeat.

18
00:01:56.491 --> 00:02:00.120
Spock. get in there. neutralize the
volcano and let's get out of here.

19
00:02:00.203 --> 00:02:01.788
(Rumbling)

20
00:02:07.127 --> 00:02:09.212
We have to do this now!
I told the captain

21
00:02:09.296 --> 00:02:11.381
the shuttle wasn't built
for this kind of heat.

22
00:02:11.632 --> 00:02:13.842
Captain. did the indigenous
life forms see you?

23
00:02:14.051 --> 00:02:15.719
No. Mr. Spock. they did not.

24
00:02:15.969 --> 00:02:17.155
The prime directive clearly states

25
00:02:17.179 --> 00:02:18.388
there can be no interference

26
00:02:18.472 --> 00:02:20.552
with the internal development
of alien civilizations.

27
00:02:20.724 --> 00:02:22.201
I know what it says!
Which is why I'm running

28
00:02:22.225 --> 00:02:23.745
through the jungle wearing a disguise!

29
00:02:23.977 --> 00:02:28.398
Now drop off your super ice cube
and let's go! Kirk out!

30
00:02:28.649 --> 00:02:29.816
You're good.

31
00:02:30.067 --> 00:02:32.147
Sulu: If we're gonna do this.
we've got to do it now!

32
00:02:32.653 --> 00:02:34.363
This ash is killing our coils.

33
00:02:34.571 --> 00:02:36.049
You sure you don't want me
to go instead?

34
00:02:36.073 --> 00:02:38.301
That would be highly illogical
as I am already outfitted...

35
00:02:38.325 --> 00:02:39.743
Spock. I was kidding.

36
00:02:41.078 --> 00:02:43.830
- You got this.
- Guys! We have to go! Now!

37
00:02:44.915 --> 00:02:47.125
- (Both panting)
- (Natives yelling)

38
00:02:53.256 --> 00:02:55.258
They're trying to kill us!

39
00:02:56.093 --> 00:02:57.678
They're trying to kill us. Jim!

40
00:02:58.261 --> 00:02:59.388
I'll see you in 90 seconds.

41
00:03:04.935 --> 00:03:06.520
Do it. do it!

42
00:03:15.904 --> 00:03:17.572
(Breathing heavily)

43
00:03:22.828 --> 00:03:24.828
Automated male voice:
Prerequisite change. 2-7-3...

44
00:03:27.916 --> 00:03:29.418
I can't hold this position.

45
00:03:29.584 --> 00:03:30.978
Spock. I've got to pull you back up.

46
00:03:31.002 --> 00:03:33.672
Negative. This is our only
chance to save this species.

47
00:03:33.922 --> 00:03:35.522
If this volcano erupts. the planet dies.

48
00:03:38.260 --> 00:03:40.345
Pull him back up. Now!

49
00:03:46.977 --> 00:03:47.978
(Grunts)

50
00:03:54.401 --> 00:03:56.903
Uhura: Spock. are you okay?

51
00:04:02.325 --> 00:04:03.744
I am.

52
00:04:03.827 --> 00:04:06.621
surprisingly. alive. Stand by.

53
00:04:06.788 --> 00:04:08.975
We have to get him back.
I'll suit up. I'm gonna go down.

54
00:04:08.999 --> 00:04:10.226
We have to abandon the shuttle.

55
00:04:10.250 --> 00:04:12.270
- We can't just leave him. sulu!
- We don't have a choice!

56
00:04:12.294 --> 00:04:13.628
Uhura. I'm sorry.

57
00:04:14.337 --> 00:04:15.815
Spock. we're going back
to the enterprise.

58
00:04:15.839 --> 00:04:16.919
We'll get you out of there.

59
00:04:17.007 --> 00:04:18.675
Captain. I'm ditching the shuttle.

60
00:04:18.759 --> 00:04:20.486
You've got to make it
to the enterprise on your own.

61
00:04:20.510 --> 00:04:21.845
Kirk: Wonderful!

62
00:04:21.970 --> 00:04:24.431
- Uhura! You ready to swim?
- I'm ready.

63
00:04:24.598 --> 00:04:26.308
(Natives clamoring)

64
00:04:26.683 --> 00:04:27.684
Jim!

65
00:04:28.602 --> 00:04:31.521
Jim! The beach is that way!

66
00:04:31.813 --> 00:04:33.493
Kirk: I know!
We're not going to the beach!

67
00:04:33.607 --> 00:04:35.275
Bones: Oh. no. no. no!

68
00:04:35.400 --> 00:04:38.028
(Natives speaking
with reverence)

69
00:04:39.613 --> 00:04:41.198
I hate this!

70
00:04:41.531 --> 00:04:42.532
I know you do!

71
00:04:42.699 --> 00:04:44.201
(Both panting)

72
00:04:48.789 --> 00:04:50.081
(Both scream)

73
00:05:25.534 --> 00:05:27.369
Do you have any idea
how ridiculous it is

74
00:05:27.410 --> 00:05:28.888
to hide a starship
on the bottom of the ocean?

75
00:05:28.912 --> 00:05:30.389
We've been down here since last night!

76
00:05:30.413 --> 00:05:31.773
The salt water's gonna ruin the...

77
00:05:31.915 --> 00:05:33.708
Scotty! Where's Spock?

78
00:05:33.834 --> 00:05:34.874
Still in the volcano. sir.

79
00:05:34.960 --> 00:05:36.044
(Sighs)

80
00:05:39.381 --> 00:05:41.091
(Breathing heavily)

81
00:05:41.758 --> 00:05:43.051
(Groaning)

82
00:06:03.446 --> 00:06:05.115
(Natives exclaiming in surprise)

83
00:06:05.240 --> 00:06:06.616
(Screaming)

84
00:06:16.334 --> 00:06:18.253
Chekov: Captain on the bridge!

85
00:06:18.503 --> 00:06:21.006
Lieutenant. do we have
an open channel to Mr. Spock?

86
00:06:21.131 --> 00:06:23.341
The heat's frying his comms.
but we still have contact.

87
00:06:25.385 --> 00:06:26.678
Spock?

88
00:06:26.803 --> 00:06:28.972
I have activated the device. captain.

89
00:06:29.014 --> 00:06:30.116
When the countdown is complete.

90
00:06:30.140 --> 00:06:31.826
the reaction should
render the volcano inert.

91
00:06:31.850 --> 00:06:33.286
Bones: Yeah. and that's
gonna render him inert!

92
00:06:33.310 --> 00:06:34.495
Do we have use of the transporters?

93
00:06:34.519 --> 00:06:36.289
- Negative. sir.
- Not with these magnetic fields.

94
00:06:36.313 --> 00:06:37.957
Kirk: I need to beam Spock
back to the ship.

95
00:06:37.981 --> 00:06:39.524
Give me one way to do it.

96
00:06:39.774 --> 00:06:41.818
Maybe if we had a direct line of sight.

97
00:06:41.860 --> 00:06:43.129
- If we got closer...
- Scotty: Hold on. wee man!

98
00:06:43.153 --> 00:06:44.713
You're talking about an active volcano!

99
00:06:44.738 --> 00:06:46.323
Sir. if that thing erupts.

100
00:06:46.406 --> 00:06:48.166
I cannae guarantee
we can withstand the heat!

101
00:06:48.241 --> 00:06:50.344
I don't know that we can
maintain that kind of altitude.

102
00:06:50.368 --> 00:06:51.971
Our shuttle was concealed
by the ash cloud.

103
00:06:51.995 --> 00:06:53.330
but the enterprise is too large.

104
00:06:53.538 --> 00:06:55.415
If utilized in a rescue effort.

105
00:06:55.582 --> 00:06:57.310
it would be revealed
to the indigenous species.

106
00:06:57.334 --> 00:06:59.134
Spock. nobody knows
the rules better than you.

107
00:06:59.169 --> 00:07:01.004
but there has got to be an exception.

108
00:07:01.171 --> 00:07:03.340
None. Such action violates
the prime directive.

109
00:07:03.506 --> 00:07:05.466
Shut up. Spock! We're trying
to save you. damn it!

110
00:07:05.550 --> 00:07:08.261
Doctor. the needs of
the many outweigh the needs of the few.

111
00:07:08.428 --> 00:07:10.472
Spock. we're talking about your life!

112
00:07:10.680 --> 00:07:12.961
- Spock: The rule cannot be broken...
- (Line disconnects)

113
00:07:13.016 --> 00:07:14.225
Kirk: Spock!

114
00:07:14.559 --> 00:07:15.639
Try to get him back online.

115
00:07:16.394 --> 00:07:18.730
Chekov: Ninety seconds
to detonations.

116
00:07:19.898 --> 00:07:23.401
If Spock were here and I were there.
what would he do?

117
00:07:26.404 --> 00:07:28.073
He'd let you die.

118
00:07:31.868 --> 00:07:33.536
(Breathing heavily)

119
00:07:54.849 --> 00:07:56.351
(All chanting)

120
00:07:57.435 --> 00:07:58.853
(Explosion)

121
00:08:01.856 --> 00:08:03.900
(All clamoring)

122
00:08:07.445 --> 00:08:09.698
(Natives exclaiming in shock)

123
00:08:17.247 --> 00:08:18.581
(Shouting)

124
00:08:22.794 --> 00:08:24.087
(Gasping in awe)

125
00:08:27.966 --> 00:08:29.509
(All clamoring)

126
00:08:42.147 --> 00:08:43.898
(Breathing heavily)

127
00:08:49.487 --> 00:08:50.488
(Beeping)

128
00:09:04.794 --> 00:09:06.129
(Breathing heavily)

129
00:09:08.798 --> 00:09:09.799
(Door opening)

130
00:09:09.966 --> 00:09:11.301
Spock!

131
00:09:11.968 --> 00:09:13.303
You all right?

132
00:09:13.803 --> 00:09:15.203
Captain. you let them see our ship.

133
00:09:15.513 --> 00:09:16.848
(Sighs) He's fine.

134
00:09:16.973 --> 00:09:18.975
- Uhura: Bridge to captain kirk.
- Yes. lieutenant.

135
00:09:19.184 --> 00:09:21.144
Is commander Spock on board. sir?

136
00:09:21.227 --> 00:09:22.788
- Kirk: Safely and soundly.
- (Relieved sigh)

137
00:09:22.812 --> 00:09:24.132
Please notify him that his device

138
00:09:24.189 --> 00:09:25.607
has successfully detonated.

139
00:09:26.649 --> 00:09:28.735
Kirk: You hear that?
Congratulations. Spock.

140
00:09:29.819 --> 00:09:31.154
You just saved the world.

141
00:09:31.404 --> 00:09:33.156
You violated the prime directive.

142
00:09:33.364 --> 00:09:35.825
Oh. come on. Spock.
They saw us. Big deal.

143
00:09:35.992 --> 00:09:37.619
(All chattering excitedly)

144
00:10:20.578 --> 00:10:22.247
(Beeping)

145
00:11:13.464 --> 00:11:14.924
(Conversing indistinctly)

146
00:11:21.472 --> 00:11:22.473
(Door opens)

147
00:11:41.618 --> 00:11:43.077
(Woman sniffles)

148
00:11:49.626 --> 00:11:51.085
(Sobbing)

149
00:12:14.150 --> 00:12:15.818
Man: I can save her.

150
00:12:19.989 --> 00:12:21.658
What did you say?

151
00:12:21.866 --> 00:12:23.368
Your daughter.

152
00:12:24.494 --> 00:12:26.329
I can save her.

153
00:12:27.497 --> 00:12:28.831
Who are you?

154
00:12:38.049 --> 00:12:40.051
(Lively '90$ hip-hop
music playing)

155
00:12:43.638 --> 00:12:44.722
(Communicator beeping)

156
00:12:45.390 --> 00:12:46.849
(Panting)

157
00:12:47.350 --> 00:12:49.769
- Oh. Jim. Come on. let it go.
- (Muttering)

158
00:12:50.520 --> 00:12:51.854
Jim!

159
00:12:51.896 --> 00:12:54.774
You're not actually gonna
answer that. are you?

160
00:12:56.192 --> 00:12:59.112
Kirk: Spock. I'm telling you.
this is why he called. I can feel it.

161
00:12:59.529 --> 00:13:01.781
Your feeling aside.
I consider it highly unlikely

162
00:13:01.864 --> 00:13:04.033
that we will be selected
for the new program.

163
00:13:04.242 --> 00:13:06.411
Why else would pike want to see us?

164
00:13:06.744 --> 00:13:07.870
Forget about seniority.

165
00:13:07.954 --> 00:13:09.390
They gave us the newest ship
in the fleet.

166
00:13:09.414 --> 00:13:10.641
I mean. who else
are they gonna send out?

167
00:13:10.665 --> 00:13:11.934
Spock: I can think of
numerous possibilities.

168
00:13:11.958 --> 00:13:13.960
A five-year mission. Spock!

169
00:13:14.419 --> 00:13:16.421
That's deep space!
That's uncharted territory!

170
00:13:16.504 --> 00:13:17.940
Think how incredible that's gonna be.

171
00:13:17.964 --> 00:13:20.174
Hey. ladies. Jim kirk.

172
00:13:21.217 --> 00:13:23.303
- "Uneventful."
- kirk: Admiral?

173
00:13:23.386 --> 00:13:26.073
It's the way you described the survey of
nibiru in your captain's log.

174
00:13:26.097 --> 00:13:28.367
Yes. sir. I didn't want to waste your time
going over the details.

175
00:13:28.391 --> 00:13:30.268
Tell me more about this volcano.

176
00:13:30.351 --> 00:13:31.728
Data says it was highly volatile.

177
00:13:31.853 --> 00:13:33.497
If it were to erupt.
it would wipe out the planet.

178
00:13:33.521 --> 00:13:34.731
Let's hope it doesn't. sir.

179
00:13:34.897 --> 00:13:36.065
Something tells me it won't.

180
00:13:36.983 --> 00:13:39.152
Well. sir. volatile is all relative.

181
00:13:39.235 --> 00:13:40.903
Maybe our data was off.

182
00:13:41.237 --> 00:13:42.238
Or maybe it didn't erupt

183
00:13:42.363 --> 00:13:44.907
because Mr. Spock detonated
a cold fusion device

184
00:13:45.074 --> 00:13:47.285
inside it right after a civilization

185
00:13:47.368 --> 00:13:49.579
that's barely invented the wheel

186
00:13:49.746 --> 00:13:52.582
happened to see a starship
rising out of their ocean!

187
00:13:52.665 --> 00:13:54.834
That is pretty much how
you describe it. is it not?

188
00:13:55.084 --> 00:13:56.711
- Admiral...
- You filed a report?

189
00:13:56.753 --> 00:13:57.879
Why didn't you tell me?

190
00:13:57.920 --> 00:14:00.720
I incorrectly assumed that you would be
truthful in your captain's log.

191
00:14:00.757 --> 00:14:03.068
Yeah. I would have been
if I didn't have to save your life.

192
00:14:03.092 --> 00:14:04.236
A fact for which I am
immeasurably grateful

193
00:14:04.260 --> 00:14:05.820
and the very reason I felt it necessary

194
00:14:05.887 --> 00:14:07.156
to take responsibility for the actions...

195
00:14:07.180 --> 00:14:08.681
(Scoffs)
Take responsibility. yeah.

196
00:14:08.765 --> 00:14:09.825
That'd be so noble. pointy.

197
00:14:09.849 --> 00:14:11.410
if you weren't also
throwing me under the bus.

198
00:14:11.434 --> 00:14:13.436
"Pointy"? Is that
a derogatory reference to...

199
00:14:13.603 --> 00:14:14.771
Gentlemen.

200
00:14:15.146 --> 00:14:19.025
Starfleet's mandate is to explore and
observe. not to interfere.

201
00:14:19.192 --> 00:14:21.072
Had the mission gone
according to plan. admiral.

202
00:14:21.110 --> 00:14:22.338
the indigenous species would never

203
00:14:22.362 --> 00:14:23.589
have been aware of our interference.

204
00:14:23.613 --> 00:14:24.822
That's a technicality.

205
00:14:24.906 --> 00:14:26.741
I am vulcan. sir.
We embrace technicality.

206
00:14:26.824 --> 00:14:28.451
Are you giving me attitude. Spock?

207
00:14:28.618 --> 00:14:30.471
I'm expressing
multiple attitudes simultaneously. sir.

208
00:14:30.495 --> 00:14:31.704
To which are you referring?

209
00:14:31.871 --> 00:14:32.955
Out.

210
00:14:33.831 --> 00:14:35.583
You're dismissed. commander.

211
00:14:42.048 --> 00:14:43.299
(Door opens)

212
00:14:44.008 --> 00:14:47.178
You have any idea what
a pain in the ass you are?

213
00:14:48.012 --> 00:14:49.180
I think so. sir.

214
00:14:49.430 --> 00:14:50.574
So tell me what you did wrong.

215
00:14:50.598 --> 00:14:52.517
What's the lesson to be learned here?

216
00:14:52.934 --> 00:14:54.102
Never trust a vulcan.

217
00:14:54.185 --> 00:14:56.729
Now. see. you can't
even answer the question. You lied.

218
00:14:56.813 --> 00:14:58.731
On an official report. you lied.

219
00:14:58.815 --> 00:15:00.292
You think the rules don't apply to you

220
00:15:00.316 --> 00:15:01.516
'cause you disagree with them.

221
00:15:01.651 --> 00:15:03.504
That's why you talked me
into signing up in the first place.

222
00:15:03.528 --> 00:15:04.768
It's why you gave me your ship.

223
00:15:04.987 --> 00:15:07.990
I gave you my ship because
I saw a greatness in you.

224
00:15:08.908 --> 00:15:11.577
And now. I see you haven't
got an ounce of humility.

225
00:15:11.661 --> 00:15:12.971
What was I supposed to do.
let Spock die?

226
00:15:12.995 --> 00:15:14.122
You're missing the point.

227
00:15:14.205 --> 00:15:15.891
I don't think I am. sir.
What would you have done?

228
00:15:15.915 --> 00:15:17.715
I wouldn't have risked
my first officer's life

229
00:15:17.792 --> 00:15:19.085
in the first place!

230
00:15:19.252 --> 00:15:21.087
You were supposed to survey a planet.

231
00:15:21.170 --> 00:15:23.005
not alter its destiny!

232
00:15:23.172 --> 00:15:25.174
You violated a dozen
starfleet regulations

233
00:15:25.258 --> 00:15:27.427
and almost got everyone
under your command killed.

234
00:15:27.635 --> 00:15:28.970
Except I didn't!

235
00:15:29.053 --> 00:15:30.447
You know how many
crew members I've lost? Not one!

236
00:15:30.471 --> 00:15:32.473
That's your problem.
you think you're infallible!

237
00:15:32.557 --> 00:15:33.909
You think you can't make a mistake.

238
00:15:33.933 --> 00:15:35.059
It's a pattern with you!

239
00:15:35.143 --> 00:15:37.395
- The rules are for other people!
- Some should be.

240
00:15:37.478 --> 00:15:39.188
And what's worse is you using blind luck

241
00:15:39.272 --> 00:15:41.357
to justify your playing god!

242
00:15:44.485 --> 00:15:45.820
Given the circumstances.

243
00:15:45.862 --> 00:15:47.881
this has been brought to
admiral Marcus's attention.

244
00:15:47.905 --> 00:15:50.700
He convened a special tribunal.
to which I was not invited.

245
00:15:50.783 --> 00:15:53.536
You understand what starfleet
regulations mandate

246
00:15:53.619 --> 00:15:54.704
be done at this point.

247
00:15:58.749 --> 00:16:00.751
They've taken the enterprise
away from you.

248
00:16:01.961 --> 00:16:04.046
They're sending you
back to the academy.

249
00:16:09.177 --> 00:16:10.261
Admiral. listen...

250
00:16:10.344 --> 00:16:11.488
- No. I'm not going to listen.
- I can justify...

251
00:16:11.512 --> 00:16:12.573
Why should I listen?
I'm not going to listen.

252
00:16:12.597 --> 00:16:13.824
You don't listen to anybody but yourself!

253
00:16:13.848 --> 00:16:15.701
I understand regulation.
but every decision I've made...

254
00:16:15.725 --> 00:16:16.726
No! I can't listen!

255
00:16:16.893 --> 00:16:18.519
You don't comply with the rules.

256
00:16:18.603 --> 00:16:20.730
you don't take responsibility
for anything.

257
00:16:20.813 --> 00:16:22.857
and you don't respect the chair.

258
00:16:24.901 --> 00:16:26.402
You know why?

259
00:16:27.570 --> 00:16:29.405
Because you're not ready for it.

260
00:17:18.204 --> 00:17:19.497
(Breathing heavily)

261
00:17:37.807 --> 00:17:39.100
(Beeping)

262
00:18:03.541 --> 00:18:06.168
(Indistinct conversations)

263
00:18:20.182 --> 00:18:22.143
(Machine humming)

264
00:18:22.226 --> 00:18:23.227
(Door opens)

265
00:18:35.072 --> 00:18:36.616
Man: (On pa)
Attention. personnel.

266
00:18:36.699 --> 00:18:38.939
Blue security clearance now
permitted for airlock access.

267
00:18:39.201 --> 00:18:41.162
Woman: I'm going to need
three titanium...

268
00:18:41.203 --> 00:18:44.165
Automated male voice: Radiation
protection is required in this area.

269
00:18:44.957 --> 00:18:47.293
(Chattering continues
indistinctly)

270
00:18:55.176 --> 00:18:56.177
(Computer beeps)

271
00:19:05.603 --> 00:19:06.604
(Whining)

272
00:19:14.403 --> 00:19:16.072
(People screaming)

273
00:19:21.661 --> 00:19:24.205
(Mellow blues music playing)

274
00:19:28.709 --> 00:19:30.127
(Clears throat)

275
00:19:34.965 --> 00:19:36.050
(Exhales)

276
00:19:47.019 --> 00:19:48.229
(Sighs)

277
00:19:51.607 --> 00:19:52.692
How did you find me?

278
00:19:52.942 --> 00:19:54.944
I know you better than you think I do.

279
00:19:57.613 --> 00:19:59.865
The first time I found you
was in a dive like this.

280
00:20:01.033 --> 00:20:03.869
Remember that? You got
your ass handed to you.

281
00:20:04.120 --> 00:20:05.204
No. I didn't.

282
00:20:05.454 --> 00:20:07.206
- You don't?
- No. that's not what happened.

283
00:20:07.289 --> 00:20:09.709
- That was an epic beating.
- No. it wasn't.

284
00:20:09.792 --> 00:20:11.794
You had napkins
hanging out of your nose.

285
00:20:12.461 --> 00:20:13.963
- (Chuckles)
- Did you not?

286
00:20:15.965 --> 00:20:17.967
Yeah. that was a good fight.

287
00:20:18.801 --> 00:20:20.469
"A good fight."

288
00:20:23.389 --> 00:20:25.725
I think that's your problem right there.

289
00:20:30.563 --> 00:20:32.398
They gave her back to me.

290
00:20:33.232 --> 00:20:34.567
The enterprise.

291
00:20:46.162 --> 00:20:47.329
Congratulations.

292
00:20:50.249 --> 00:20:52.585
Watch your back with
that first officer. though.

293
00:20:54.253 --> 00:20:55.813
Spock's not going
to be working with me.

294
00:20:55.838 --> 00:20:57.339
He's been transferred.

295
00:20:58.257 --> 00:20:59.925
U. S. S. Bradbury.

296
00:21:02.303 --> 00:21:04.305
You're going to be my first officer.

297
00:21:05.181 --> 00:21:07.516
Yeah. Marcus took some convincing.

298
00:21:09.101 --> 00:21:12.146
But every now and then
I can make a good case.

299
00:21:15.441 --> 00:21:16.942
What did you tell him?

300
00:21:17.568 --> 00:21:18.736
The truth.

301
00:21:19.487 --> 00:21:21.238
That I believe in you.

302
00:21:22.990 --> 00:21:26.327
That if anybody
deserves a second chance. it's Jim kirk.

303
00:21:34.251 --> 00:21:35.544
(Sighs)

304
00:21:36.086 --> 00:21:37.671
I don't know what to say.

305
00:21:38.756 --> 00:21:40.216
That is a first.

306
00:21:42.092 --> 00:21:43.886
It's going to be okay. son.

307
00:21:45.763 --> 00:21:46.931
(Communicator beeps)

308
00:21:49.809 --> 00:21:51.060
(Chirps)

309
00:21:51.352 --> 00:21:53.062
"Emergency session. daystrom."

310
00:21:54.647 --> 00:21:55.856
That's us.

311
00:21:56.357 --> 00:21:57.483
Yeah.

312
00:21:58.442 --> 00:21:59.777
Suit up.

313
00:22:11.497 --> 00:22:14.250
Woman: (On pa) All starfleet
personnel. please be advised.

314
00:22:14.375 --> 00:22:17.253
- new security protocols are in effect.
- Spock: Captain.

315
00:22:17.419 --> 00:22:19.421
Not anymore. Spock. First officer.

316
00:22:20.840 --> 00:22:23.259
I was demoted
and you were reassigned.

317
00:22:23.592 --> 00:22:25.094
It is fortunate that the consequences

318
00:22:25.177 --> 00:22:26.262
were not more severe.

319
00:22:26.345 --> 00:22:27.739
(Sighs) You've got to be kidding me.

320
00:22:27.763 --> 00:22:28.907
Captain. it was never my intention...

321
00:22:28.931 --> 00:22:30.099
Not captain.

322
00:22:30.432 --> 00:22:31.517
I saved your life. Spock.

323
00:22:31.600 --> 00:22:33.936
You wrote a report. I lost my ship.

324
00:22:35.688 --> 00:22:38.482
Commander. I see now
I should have alerted you

325
00:22:38.566 --> 00:22:40.234
to the fact that I submitted the report.

326
00:22:40.317 --> 00:22:42.152
Kirk: No. I'm familiar
with your compulsion

327
00:22:42.403 --> 00:22:44.947
to follow the rules.
But you see. I can't do that.

328
00:22:45.614 --> 00:22:47.658
Where I come from.
if someone saves your life.

329
00:22:47.741 --> 00:22:48.981
you don't stab him in the back.

330
00:22:49.118 --> 00:22:50.744
Vulcans cannot lie.

331
00:22:50.953 --> 00:22:52.639
Then I'm talking
to the half-human part of you.

332
00:22:52.663 --> 00:22:54.164
All right?

333
00:22:54.415 --> 00:22:56.709
Do you understand
why I went back for you?

334
00:22:56.917 --> 00:23:00.254
Commander Spock?
Frank Abbot. u. S. S. Bradbury.

335
00:23:00.462 --> 00:23:01.797
Guess you're with me.

336
00:23:03.632 --> 00:23:04.967
Yes. captain.

337
00:23:12.641 --> 00:23:14.226
The truth is

338
00:23:16.145 --> 00:23:17.646
I'm going to miss you.

339
00:23:24.153 --> 00:23:25.153
(Sighs in frustration)

340
00:23:25.863 --> 00:23:28.324
Abbot: Admiral Marcus. sir.

341
00:23:29.241 --> 00:23:32.494
Thank you for convening
on such short notice.

342
00:23:32.536 --> 00:23:33.787
Be seated.

343
00:23:35.998 --> 00:23:38.667
By now. some of you
have heard what happened in London.

344
00:23:38.876 --> 00:23:41.170
The target was a starfleet data archive.

345
00:23:41.295 --> 00:23:42.480
Now it's a damned hole in the ground.

346
00:23:42.504 --> 00:23:44.173
42 men and women are dead.

347
00:23:44.465 --> 00:23:45.549
One hour ago.

348
00:23:45.633 --> 00:23:47.433
I received a message
from a starfleet officer.

349
00:23:47.551 --> 00:23:49.345
who confessed to
carrying out this attack.

350
00:23:49.845 --> 00:23:52.181
that he was being
forced to do it by this man.

351
00:23:52.264 --> 00:23:55.184
commander John Harrison.
He's one of our own.

352
00:23:55.517 --> 00:23:58.354
And he is the man responsible
for this act of savagery.

353
00:23:59.355 --> 00:24:01.124
For reasons unknown.
John Harrison has just declared

354
00:24:01.148 --> 00:24:03.609
a one-man war against starfleet.

355
00:24:04.151 --> 00:24:07.529
And under no circumstances
are we to allow this man

356
00:24:07.571 --> 00:24:09.156
to escape federation space.

357
00:24:10.074 --> 00:24:11.676
You here tonight represent
the senior command

358
00:24:11.700 --> 00:24:13.410
of all the vessels in the region.

359
00:24:13.827 --> 00:24:16.163
And in the name of those we lost.

360
00:24:16.205 --> 00:24:18.499
you will run this bastard down.

361
00:24:19.208 --> 00:24:22.836
This is a manhunt.
pure and simple. so let's get to work.

362
00:24:23.253 --> 00:24:25.255
Earth's perimeter sensors
have not detected

363
00:24:25.339 --> 00:24:26.966
any warp signatures leaving the system.

364
00:24:27.049 --> 00:24:28.342
so we know he can't be far.

365
00:24:29.551 --> 00:24:31.720
You will park your ships
in a blockade formation

366
00:24:31.887 --> 00:24:34.223
then deploy search vehicles
and landing parties

367
00:24:34.306 --> 00:24:37.101
to run down every lead.

368
00:24:37.309 --> 00:24:39.120
This man has shown willingness
to kill innocent people.

369
00:24:39.144 --> 00:24:41.647
so the rules of engagement are simple.

370
00:24:41.730 --> 00:24:44.733
If you come across this man
and fear for your life

371
00:24:44.858 --> 00:24:46.652
or the lives of those nearby.

372
00:24:46.735 --> 00:24:49.738
you are authorized to
use deadly force on sight.

373
00:24:49.863 --> 00:24:51.532
- What's in the bag?
- James. not now.

374
00:24:51.699 --> 00:24:53.859
It doesn't seem odd to you
that he'd target an archive?

375
00:24:53.909 --> 00:24:55.411
It's like bombing a library.

376
00:24:55.577 --> 00:24:57.162
Chris? Everything okay there?

377
00:24:57.538 --> 00:25:00.207
Yes. sir. Mr. Kirk is just acclimating

378
00:25:00.249 --> 00:25:02.042
to his new position as first officer.

379
00:25:02.209 --> 00:25:03.836
You got something to say. kirk. say it.

380
00:25:03.919 --> 00:25:05.504
Tomorrow's too late.

381
00:25:07.589 --> 00:25:08.709
I'm fine. sir. My apologies.

382
00:25:09.258 --> 00:25:11.677
Spit it out. son. Don't be shy.

383
00:25:12.928 --> 00:25:14.930
Why the archive?

384
00:25:15.431 --> 00:25:17.766
All that information is public record.

385
00:25:17.850 --> 00:25:19.852
If he really wanted to damage starfleet.

386
00:25:22.062 --> 00:25:23.647
this could just be the beginning.

387
00:25:23.814 --> 00:25:25.274
The beginning of what. Mr. Kirk?

388
00:25:25.482 --> 00:25:28.235
Sir. in the event
of an attack. protocol mandates

389
00:25:28.277 --> 00:25:31.196
that senior command gather
captains and first officers

390
00:25:31.280 --> 00:25:33.282
at starfleet h.Q.. right here

391
00:25:34.783 --> 00:25:36.702
- in this room.
- Spock: It is curious Harrison

392
00:25:36.910 --> 00:25:39.110
would commandeer a jumpship
without warp capabilities...

393
00:25:39.580 --> 00:25:41.457
(Rumbling)

394
00:25:45.127 --> 00:25:46.128
Clear the room!

395
00:25:46.587 --> 00:25:47.921
(All screaming)

396
00:25:48.130 --> 00:25:49.381
(Grunting)

397
00:25:49.840 --> 00:25:51.258
(Turrets firing)

398
00:25:51.383 --> 00:25:52.468
Woman: No!

399
00:25:52.968 --> 00:25:53.969
(Screams)

400
00:25:54.428 --> 00:25:57.264
We need an air defense team!
Daystrom conference room!

401
00:25:57.473 --> 00:25:58.891
(Clamoring continues)

402
00:25:58.974 --> 00:26:00.535
- Guard 1: Let's go!
- Guard 2: Cover me!

403
00:26:00.559 --> 00:26:01.894
(Both groaning)

404
00:26:03.020 --> 00:26:05.147
(Panting)

405
00:26:09.068 --> 00:26:10.754
Guard 1: Target acquired.
Guard 2: Take him out!

406
00:26:10.778 --> 00:26:11.779
Guard 1: Watch my flank!

407
00:26:13.322 --> 00:26:15.657
Guard 3: Go. go. go!
Guard 4: Cover me!

408
00:26:22.748 --> 00:26:23.749
(Breathing heavily)

409
00:26:27.002 --> 00:26:28.003
(Grunts)

410
00:26:34.468 --> 00:26:35.803
(Groaning)

411
00:26:52.194 --> 00:26:53.362
(Grunts)

412
00:26:55.155 --> 00:26:56.198
(Pike groaning)

413
00:26:57.574 --> 00:26:58.575
(Grunts)

414
00:26:59.576 --> 00:27:00.577
Guard 1: Fire!

415
00:27:01.995 --> 00:27:03.330
(Pike wheezing)

416
00:27:06.708 --> 00:27:07.709
(Gasping)

417
00:27:16.468 --> 00:27:17.719
(Grunts)

418
00:27:31.817 --> 00:27:33.235
- (Grinding)
- (Engine sputtering)

419
00:28:00.804 --> 00:28:02.514
(Pike breathing heavily)

420
00:28:50.812 --> 00:28:52.231
(Sobbing)

421
00:29:40.237 --> 00:29:42.072
(Sirens wailing)

422
00:29:55.085 --> 00:29:56.545
(Thunder crashing)

423
00:30:15.522 --> 00:30:17.065
(Communicator beeping)

424
00:30:21.486 --> 00:30:22.654
(Communicator chirps)

425
00:30:22.738 --> 00:30:23.822
Yeah?

426
00:30:23.905 --> 00:30:26.408
Spock: Commander.
Mr. Scott has found something

427
00:30:26.533 --> 00:30:28.368
in the wreckage of Harrison's ship.

428
00:30:28.702 --> 00:30:31.038
He has asked to see us right away.

429
00:30:32.831 --> 00:30:35.876
Scotty: Captain!
I found this in the crashed jumpship. sir.

430
00:30:35.917 --> 00:30:37.770
- This is how the bastard got away.
- Kirk: What do you mean?

431
00:30:37.794 --> 00:30:39.921
Scotty: It's a portable
transwarp beaming device.

432
00:30:40.005 --> 00:30:41.399
Kirk: Well. can you figure out
where he went?

433
00:30:41.423 --> 00:30:44.259
I already did. sir.
And you're no gonna like it.

434
00:30:44.301 --> 00:30:45.344
(Device beeps)

435
00:30:45.594 --> 00:30:47.262
He's gone to the one place we...

436
00:30:47.763 --> 00:30:49.598
We just can't go.

437
00:30:52.184 --> 00:30:54.102
Admiral. sir. he's not on earth.

438
00:30:56.021 --> 00:30:58.523
(Panting) He's on kronos. sir.

439
00:30:58.607 --> 00:31:00.192
I request my command be reinstated

440
00:31:00.275 --> 00:31:02.110
and your permission to go after him.

441
00:31:03.612 --> 00:31:04.780
Give us a minute.

442
00:31:06.281 --> 00:31:07.407
- Kronos.
- Yes. sir.

443
00:31:07.449 --> 00:31:09.951
So Harrison's gone
to the klingon homeworld.

444
00:31:10.077 --> 00:31:11.745
- Is he defecting?
- We're not sure. sir.

445
00:31:11.787 --> 00:31:13.264
He has taken refuge
in the ketha province.

446
00:31:13.288 --> 00:31:14.390
a region uninhabited for decades.

447
00:31:14.414 --> 00:31:15.916
He's gotta be hiding there. sir!

448
00:31:15.957 --> 00:31:17.709
He knows if we even
go near klingon space.

449
00:31:17.793 --> 00:31:18.794
it'd be all-out war.

450
00:31:18.877 --> 00:31:21.129
Starfleet can't go after him. but I can.

451
00:31:22.089 --> 00:31:23.423
Please. sir.

452
00:31:25.592 --> 00:31:28.261
All-out war with
the klingons is inevitable. Mr. Kirk.

453
00:31:28.303 --> 00:31:29.679
If you ask me. it's already begun.

454
00:31:29.930 --> 00:31:31.449
Since we first learned of their existence.

455
00:31:31.473 --> 00:31:33.600
the klingon empire
has conquered and occupied

456
00:31:33.642 --> 00:31:34.810
two planets that we know of

457
00:31:34.935 --> 00:31:37.437
and fired on our ships
half a dozen times.

458
00:31:39.564 --> 00:31:41.108
They are coming our way.

459
00:31:42.984 --> 00:31:45.153
London was not an archive.

460
00:31:45.487 --> 00:31:47.155
It was a top-secret branch of starfleet

461
00:31:47.239 --> 00:31:49.741
designated section 31.

462
00:31:49.950 --> 00:31:51.427
They were developing
defense technology

463
00:31:51.451 --> 00:31:53.370
and training our officers
to gather intelligence

464
00:31:53.495 --> 00:31:55.056
on the klingons
and any other potential enemy

465
00:31:55.080 --> 00:31:57.290
who means to do us harm.

466
00:31:57.416 --> 00:31:58.834
Harrison was one of our top agents.

467
00:31:59.000 --> 00:32:01.253
Well. now he's a fugitive
and I want to take him out.

468
00:32:03.088 --> 00:32:05.799
Pike always said you were
one of our best and brightest.

469
00:32:06.425 --> 00:32:08.677
You should have heard him defend you.

470
00:32:09.553 --> 00:32:11.993
He's the one who talked you
into joining starfleet. wasn't he?

471
00:32:12.931 --> 00:32:14.099
Yes. sir.

472
00:32:14.641 --> 00:32:16.852
Did he ever tell you
who talked him into joining?

473
00:32:19.646 --> 00:32:20.981
(Clicks tongue)

474
00:32:21.106 --> 00:32:23.108
His death is on me.

475
00:32:24.693 --> 00:32:25.694
And yours can't be.

476
00:32:25.861 --> 00:32:26.862
Sir. please. All I...

477
00:32:26.987 --> 00:32:28.530
Mr. Spock. you said the province

478
00:32:28.655 --> 00:32:30.133
where Harrison is hiding is uninhabited?

479
00:32:30.157 --> 00:32:31.658
Affirmative. sir.

480
00:32:34.870 --> 00:32:36.663
As part of our defensive strategy.

481
00:32:36.705 --> 00:32:38.999
31 developed a new photon torpedo.

482
00:32:39.666 --> 00:32:41.126
(Beeping)

483
00:32:41.626 --> 00:32:43.044
Long-range and untraceable.

484
00:32:43.170 --> 00:32:45.297
it would be invisible to klingon sensors.

485
00:32:45.547 --> 00:32:48.550
I don't want you hurt.
but I want to take him out.

486
00:32:48.633 --> 00:32:50.510
You park on the edge
of the neutral zone.

487
00:32:50.552 --> 00:32:52.471
you lock onto Harrison's position.

488
00:32:52.554 --> 00:32:54.154
you fire. you kill him and you haul ass.

489
00:32:55.640 --> 00:32:58.810
Permission to reinstate
Mr. Spock as my first officer.

490
00:33:00.479 --> 00:33:01.480
Granted.

491
00:33:02.147 --> 00:33:04.232
(Overlapping conversations)

492
00:33:09.154 --> 00:33:10.238
Bones: Jim!

493
00:33:11.406 --> 00:33:13.158
- Where were you?
- For what?

494
00:33:13.408 --> 00:33:14.868
Your medical exam.

495
00:33:14.910 --> 00:33:16.912
Ten hours ago. you were
in a damn firefight.

496
00:33:16.995 --> 00:33:19.247
- Now it's my duty as ship's...
- I'm fine. bones.

497
00:33:19.498 --> 00:33:20.916
The hell you are.

498
00:33:23.001 --> 00:33:24.419
I'm fine.

499
00:33:29.758 --> 00:33:32.177
Kirk: Status report.
Mr. Spock. (Grunts)

500
00:33:32.260 --> 00:33:33.654
The enterprise should be
ready for launch

501
00:33:33.678 --> 00:33:35.096
by the time we arrive.

502
00:33:35.430 --> 00:33:37.432
- Good. Good.
- Captain.

503
00:33:38.850 --> 00:33:40.769
Thank you for requesting
my reinstatement.

504
00:33:42.437 --> 00:33:43.772
You're welcome.

505
00:33:44.689 --> 00:33:46.775
As I am again
your first officer. it is now my duty

506
00:33:46.900 --> 00:33:48.660
to strongly object
to our mission parameters.

507
00:33:48.944 --> 00:33:49.945
Of course it is.

508
00:33:50.070 --> 00:33:51.530
There is no starfleet regulation

509
00:33:51.613 --> 00:33:53.293
that condemns a man
to die without a trial.

510
00:33:53.323 --> 00:33:55.951
something you
and admiral Marcus are forgetting.

511
00:33:56.117 --> 00:33:58.328
Also. preemptively firing torpedoes

512
00:33:58.411 --> 00:33:59.971
at the klingon homeworld
goes against...

513
00:34:00.038 --> 00:34:01.790
You yourself said
the area's uninhabited.

514
00:34:01.831 --> 00:34:03.231
There's only gonna be one casualty.

515
00:34:03.458 --> 00:34:04.560
And in case you weren't listening.

516
00:34:04.584 --> 00:34:06.784
our orders have nothing to do
with starfleet regulation.

517
00:34:06.878 --> 00:34:08.523
Wait a minute. We're firing
torpedoes at the klingons?

518
00:34:08.547 --> 00:34:11.591
Regulations aside.
this action is morally wrong.

519
00:34:11.716 --> 00:34:14.445
Regulations aside. pulling your ass
out of a volcano was morally right.

520
00:34:14.469 --> 00:34:15.655
And I didn't win any points for that.

521
00:34:15.679 --> 00:34:16.680
Whoa. Jim. calm down.

522
00:34:16.763 --> 00:34:18.324
I'm not gonna take
ethics lessons from a robot!

523
00:34:18.348 --> 00:34:20.117
Reverting to name-calling
suggests that you are defensive

524
00:34:20.141 --> 00:34:21.494
and therefore find my opinion valid.

525
00:34:21.518 --> 00:34:22.838
I wasn't asking for your opinion.

526
00:34:23.144 --> 00:34:25.063
Bones. get that thing off my face.

527
00:34:25.146 --> 00:34:27.816
Spock: Captain. our mission
could start a war with the klingons

528
00:34:27.983 --> 00:34:29.985
and it is. by its very definition. immoral.

529
00:34:30.068 --> 00:34:31.708
Perhaps you should
take the requisite time

530
00:34:31.778 --> 00:34:34.072
to arrive at this conclusion for yourself.

531
00:34:34.155 --> 00:34:35.323
Woman: Captain kirk.

532
00:34:36.825 --> 00:34:38.159
Science officer Wallace.

533
00:34:38.243 --> 00:34:40.453
I've been assigned
to the enterprise by admiral Marcus.

534
00:34:40.996 --> 00:34:42.497
These are my transfer orders.

535
00:34:43.248 --> 00:34:45.333
You requested an additional
science officer. captain?

536
00:34:45.500 --> 00:34:46.543
I wish I had.

537
00:34:48.336 --> 00:34:50.422
"Lieutenant Carol Wallace."

538
00:34:50.589 --> 00:34:51.881
"Doctorate in applied physics

539
00:34:52.090 --> 00:34:54.926
"specializing in advanced weaponry."

540
00:34:55.010 --> 00:34:56.210
Spock: Impressive credentials.

541
00:34:56.469 --> 00:34:57.470
Thank you.

542
00:34:57.596 --> 00:34:59.198
But redundant now that
I am back aboard the enterprise.

543
00:34:59.222 --> 00:35:00.640
And yet. the more the merrier.

544
00:35:00.682 --> 00:35:02.767
- Have a seat. doctor.
- Thank you.

545
00:35:05.687 --> 00:35:08.356
Shuttle crew. stand by for lift-off.

546
00:35:29.836 --> 00:35:31.504
Scotty: No! I'm not signing anything!

547
00:35:31.546 --> 00:35:33.798
Now. get these bloody things
off my ship! Captain!

548
00:35:33.882 --> 00:35:35.109
Kirk: Is there a problem. Mr. Scott?

549
00:35:35.133 --> 00:35:37.053
Aye. sir. I was just
explaining to this gentleman

550
00:35:37.218 --> 00:35:39.721
that I cannae authorize any
weapons on board this ship

551
00:35:39.763 --> 00:35:40.948
without knowing what's inside them.

552
00:35:40.972 --> 00:35:42.766
Mr. Scott raises yet another point...

553
00:35:42.891 --> 00:35:43.975
Report to the bridge.

554
00:35:44.309 --> 00:35:45.310
Captain.

555
00:35:45.644 --> 00:35:47.395
Mr. Scott. I understand your concerns.

556
00:35:47.437 --> 00:35:49.314
but we need these torpedoes on board.

557
00:35:49.522 --> 00:35:52.025
Due respect. sir.
but photon torpedoes run on fuel.

558
00:35:52.067 --> 00:35:53.693
Now. I cannae detect the type of fuel

559
00:35:53.735 --> 00:35:55.570
that's in the compartments
on these torpedoes

560
00:35:55.654 --> 00:35:56.696
because it's shielded.

561
00:35:56.738 --> 00:35:59.074
Now. I asked for
the specifications. but he said...

562
00:35:59.407 --> 00:36:01.242
- It's classified.
- It's classified.

563
00:36:01.284 --> 00:36:03.411
So I said. "no specs. no signature!"

564
00:36:03.453 --> 00:36:04.454
Sulu: Captain.

565
00:36:04.954 --> 00:36:06.831
Flight check's complete.
We're good to go. sir.

566
00:36:06.956 --> 00:36:08.833
- Thank you. Mr. Sulu.
- Yes. sir.

567
00:36:08.958 --> 00:36:11.961
Now if you'll excuse me. sir.
I have a warp core to prime.

568
00:36:12.587 --> 00:36:13.755
Get down!

569
00:36:13.922 --> 00:36:15.423
Jim. your vitals are way off.

570
00:36:15.465 --> 00:36:17.801
Report to the med bay. Scotty!

571
00:36:17.926 --> 00:36:19.469
I need you to approve those weapons.

572
00:36:19.552 --> 00:36:20.613
Do you know what this is. captain?

573
00:36:20.637 --> 00:36:22.114
I don't have time for a lecture. Scotty.

574
00:36:22.138 --> 00:36:24.974
- Do you know what this is?
- It's a warp core.

575
00:36:25.100 --> 00:36:28.103
It's a radioactive
catastrophe waiting to happen.

576
00:36:28.311 --> 00:36:30.105
A subtle shift in magnetic output

577
00:36:30.230 --> 00:36:33.108
from. say. firing
one or more of six dozen torpedoes

578
00:36:33.274 --> 00:36:34.609
with an unknown payload

579
00:36:34.818 --> 00:36:36.253
could set off a chain reaction
which would kill

580
00:36:36.277 --> 00:36:37.946
every living thing on this ship.

581
00:36:38.113 --> 00:36:40.633
Letting those torpedoes on board the
enterprise is the last straw!

582
00:36:40.657 --> 00:36:42.450
- What was the first straw?
- What was the...

583
00:36:42.617 --> 00:36:44.411
There are plenty of straws.

584
00:36:44.452 --> 00:36:47.122
How about starfleet
confiscating my transwarp equation?

585
00:36:47.163 --> 00:36:49.457
And now some madman's
using it to hop across the galaxy!

586
00:36:49.624 --> 00:36:50.643
Where do you think he got it from?

587
00:36:50.667 --> 00:36:52.001
We have our orders. Scotty!

588
00:36:52.210 --> 00:36:53.920
That's what scares me.

589
00:36:54.337 --> 00:36:56.673
This is clearly a military operation.

590
00:36:57.006 --> 00:36:58.591
Is that what we are now?

591
00:36:58.633 --> 00:37:00.033
'Cause I thought we were explorers.

592
00:37:00.468 --> 00:37:03.138
Sign for the torpedoes. that's an order.

593
00:37:04.431 --> 00:37:06.141
Right. well. you leave me no choice

594
00:37:06.182 --> 00:37:07.475
but to resign my duties.

595
00:37:07.642 --> 00:37:09.102
Come on. Scotty.

596
00:37:09.310 --> 00:37:10.955
You're giving me no choice. sir.
I will not stand by...

597
00:37:10.979 --> 00:37:12.164
You're not giving me much of a choice.

598
00:37:12.188 --> 00:37:13.457
Will you just
make an exception and sign...

599
00:37:13.481 --> 00:37:14.921
Do you accept my resignation or not?

600
00:37:22.449 --> 00:37:23.783
I do.

601
00:37:25.994 --> 00:37:27.996
You are relieved. Mr. Scott.

602
00:37:37.839 --> 00:37:43.470
Jim. for the love of god.
do not use those torpedoes.

603
00:37:55.023 --> 00:37:56.167
Automated female voice:
Attention.

604
00:37:56.191 --> 00:37:59.110
Warp core anti-matter
containment check

605
00:37:59.235 --> 00:38:00.653
in three minutes.

606
00:38:04.491 --> 00:38:07.035
U h u ra: Captain! I'm so sorry
about admiral pike.

607
00:38:07.368 --> 00:38:08.703
We all are.

608
00:38:09.329 --> 00:38:11.206
- Are you okay?
- Fine. thank you. lieutenant.

609
00:38:15.668 --> 00:38:16.878
(Sighs)

610
00:38:19.714 --> 00:38:21.382
Actually. Scotty just quit.

611
00:38:23.343 --> 00:38:26.387
And your boyfriend's second-guessing
me every chance he gets.

612
00:38:29.516 --> 00:38:31.184
I'm sorry. that was inappropriate.

613
00:38:31.226 --> 00:38:34.896
It's just sometimes
I want to rip the bangs off his head.

614
00:38:36.356 --> 00:38:38.233
- You know. maybe it's me. I...
- It's not you.

615
00:38:40.068 --> 00:38:41.069
It's not?

616
00:38:43.738 --> 00:38:45.865
Wait. are you guys...
Are you guys fighting?

617
00:38:45.907 --> 00:38:47.009
I'd rather not talk about it. sir.

618
00:38:47.033 --> 00:38:49.077
Oh. my god! What is that even like?

619
00:38:54.707 --> 00:38:56.000
Your ears burning?

620
00:38:56.084 --> 00:38:57.284
Chekov: Captain on the bridge!

621
00:38:57.710 --> 00:38:59.003
Sulu: Captain.

622
00:38:59.712 --> 00:39:02.757
Mr. Chekov. You've been
shadowing Mr. Scott.

623
00:39:02.799 --> 00:39:05.176
You are familiar with
the engineering systems of this ship?

624
00:39:05.260 --> 00:39:06.261
Affirmative. sir.

625
00:39:06.386 --> 00:39:07.387
Good.

626
00:39:07.929 --> 00:39:11.140
You're my new chief.
Go put on a red shirt.

627
00:39:14.769 --> 00:39:16.271
Aye. captain.

628
00:39:20.400 --> 00:39:21.818
Retract all moorings. Mr. Sulu.

629
00:39:22.902 --> 00:39:24.112
Yes. sir.

630
00:39:24.362 --> 00:39:25.864
(Mechanical whirring)

631
00:39:28.449 --> 00:39:31.095
Automated female voice: Docking
clamps one. two. and three are released.

632
00:39:31.119 --> 00:39:32.879
Automated male voice:
All moorings retracted.

633
00:39:43.298 --> 00:39:44.608
Lieutenant uhura.
open a shipwide channel.

634
00:39:44.632 --> 00:39:45.633
Uhura: Yes. sir.

635
00:39:46.301 --> 00:39:48.021
Kirk: Mr. Chekov.
how we looking down there?

636
00:39:48.303 --> 00:39:50.513
- All systems nominal. captain.
- Copy that.

637
00:39:50.638 --> 00:39:52.140
Warp available at your command.

638
00:39:52.181 --> 00:39:53.808
Thank you. Mr. Chekov.

639
00:39:54.767 --> 00:39:56.436
- All right. Let's ride.
- Yes. sir.

640
00:39:56.603 --> 00:39:57.979
(Panels beeping)

641
00:40:09.282 --> 00:40:11.409
- (Radio frequencies open)
- Channel open. sir.

642
00:40:12.160 --> 00:40:14.537
Kirk: Attention. crew of the enterprise.

643
00:40:14.746 --> 00:40:16.831
As most of you know. Christopher pike.

644
00:40:16.915 --> 00:40:19.834
former captain of this ship
and our friend.

645
00:40:21.502 --> 00:40:22.962
is dead.

646
00:40:24.005 --> 00:40:25.673
The man who killed him
has fled our system

647
00:40:25.757 --> 00:40:27.508
and is hiding on the klingon homeworld.

648
00:40:27.675 --> 00:40:30.178
somewhere he believes
we are unwilling to go.

649
00:40:31.638 --> 00:40:34.182
We are on our way there now.

650
00:40:34.349 --> 00:40:38.186
Per admiral Marcus. it is essential
that our presence go undetected.

651
00:40:38.311 --> 00:40:39.896
Tensions between the federation

652
00:40:40.021 --> 00:40:41.689
and the klingon empire have been high.

653
00:40:41.814 --> 00:40:44.108
Any provocation could lead
to an all-out war.

654
00:40:57.872 --> 00:40:59.874
I will personally lead a landing party

655
00:40:59.916 --> 00:41:02.543
to an abandoned city
on the surface of kronos

656
00:41:03.336 --> 00:41:06.547
where we will capture
the fugitive. John Harrison.

657
00:41:06.756 --> 00:41:10.718
and return him to earth
so he can face judgment for his actions.

658
00:41:14.138 --> 00:41:16.933
All right. Let's go
get this son of a bitch. Kirk out.

659
00:41:22.271 --> 00:41:24.732
Captain. I believe you have
made the right decision.

660
00:41:24.816 --> 00:41:25.856
If I can be of assistance.

661
00:41:25.900 --> 00:41:27.902
I would be happy to accompany
you on the away team.

662
00:41:29.737 --> 00:41:31.698
You? Happy?

663
00:41:31.864 --> 00:41:34.534
I was simply attempting to use your
vernacular to convey an idea.

664
00:41:36.703 --> 00:41:38.413
Thank you. Mr. Spock.

665
00:41:47.088 --> 00:41:51.175
Man: (On pa) All personnel. prepare
for the closing of payload bay doors.

666
00:41:52.218 --> 00:41:53.886
(Tricorder beeping)

667
00:41:58.933 --> 00:42:01.102
Mr. Spock. You startled me.

668
00:42:02.103 --> 00:42:03.604
What are you doing. doctor?

669
00:42:03.730 --> 00:42:05.749
- Verifying that the torpedo's internal...
- You misunderstand.

670
00:42:05.773 --> 00:42:07.775
What are you doing aboard this ship?

671
00:42:07.817 --> 00:42:10.653
There is no record
of you being assigned to the enterprise.

672
00:42:10.820 --> 00:42:12.256
Really? That must be
some sort of mistake.

673
00:42:12.280 --> 00:42:14.574
My conclusion as well. Dr. Marcus.

674
00:42:15.450 --> 00:42:18.119
Except that you have lied
about your identity.

675
00:42:18.327 --> 00:42:20.747
Wallace is the surname of your mother.

676
00:42:20.788 --> 00:42:23.041
I can only assume
the admiral is your father.

677
00:42:26.419 --> 00:42:27.754
Mr. Spock.

678
00:42:28.337 --> 00:42:30.840
I'm aware that I have
no right to ask this of you.

679
00:42:31.049 --> 00:42:33.926
But please. he cannot
know that I'm here...

680
00:42:34.010 --> 00:42:35.678
(All grunting)

681
00:42:41.851 --> 00:42:44.020
Engineering manually
dropped us out of warp. sir.

682
00:42:44.145 --> 00:42:45.855
Mr. Chekov. did you break my ship?

683
00:42:45.980 --> 00:42:47.607
Sorry. sir. I don't know what happened!

684
00:42:47.648 --> 00:42:48.816
The core overheated.

685
00:42:48.858 --> 00:42:50.526
I had to activate the emergency stop.

686
00:42:50.651 --> 00:42:52.379
It must be a coolant leak.
I need time to find it.

687
00:42:52.403 --> 00:42:54.572
- Sorry. captain.
- Damn it.

688
00:42:55.031 --> 00:42:57.158
(Sighs) Mr. Sulu.
time to our destination.

689
00:42:57.366 --> 00:42:58.534
Twenty minutes. sir.

690
00:42:58.659 --> 00:43:00.804
That's 20 minutes
in enemy space we weren't counting on.

691
00:43:00.828 --> 00:43:02.497
All right. We better hop to it.

692
00:43:02.622 --> 00:43:04.082
- Where's Spock?
- Here. captain.

693
00:43:04.248 --> 00:43:06.167
You're coming with me to kronos.

694
00:43:06.209 --> 00:43:07.352
Lieutenant. how's your klingon?

695
00:43:07.376 --> 00:43:09.576
- It's rusty. but it's good.
- Good. you're coming. too.

696
00:43:10.838 --> 00:43:13.233
This isn't going to be a problem. is it.
you two working together?

697
00:43:13.257 --> 00:43:14.842
Absolutely not.

698
00:43:17.512 --> 00:43:18.513
Unclear.

699
00:43:19.430 --> 00:43:20.750
I'll meet you in the shuttle bay.

700
00:43:21.724 --> 00:43:24.143
Jim. you're not actually
going down there. are you?

701
00:43:24.227 --> 00:43:27.855
You don't Rob a bank
when the getaway car has a flat tire.

702
00:43:27.980 --> 00:43:28.981
(Radio frequencies open)

703
00:43:29.023 --> 00:43:30.584
I'm sure engineering
will have us all patched up

704
00:43:30.608 --> 00:43:31.651
by the time we get back.

705
00:43:31.859 --> 00:43:33.820
Isn't that right. Mr. Chekov?

706
00:43:33.861 --> 00:43:34.862
Yes. captain.

707
00:43:35.238 --> 00:43:37.490
- /'il do my best. sir.
- (Radio frequencies close)

708
00:43:38.366 --> 00:43:39.742
Mr. Sulu. you have the conn.

709
00:43:40.868 --> 00:43:42.548
Once we're en route.
I want you to transmit

710
00:43:42.578 --> 00:43:44.872
a targeted comm burst
to Harrison's location.

711
00:43:44.914 --> 00:43:47.518
You tell him you have a bunch
of real big torpedoes pointed at his head

712
00:43:47.542 --> 00:43:50.294
and if he doesn't play nice.
you're not afraid to use them.

713
00:43:50.545 --> 00:43:52.255
- Is that a problem?
- No. sir.

714
00:43:52.505 --> 00:43:54.215
I've just never sat in the chair before.

715
00:43:55.508 --> 00:43:57.009
You're gonna do great.

716
00:43:58.678 --> 00:44:00.179
(Softly) Jim! Wait!

717
00:44:00.304 --> 00:44:02.849
You just sat that man down
at a high-stakes poker game

718
00:44:02.890 --> 00:44:05.059
with no cards and told him to bluff.

719
00:44:05.184 --> 00:44:07.520
Now sulu's a good man.
but he is no captain.

720
00:44:07.728 --> 00:44:08.872
For the next two hours. he is.

721
00:44:08.896 --> 00:44:11.041
And enough with the metaphors.
all right? That's an order.

722
00:44:11.065 --> 00:44:13.505
Kirk: Mr. Sulu. make sure
that k'normian ship is ready to fly.

723
00:44:21.909 --> 00:44:23.202
(Radio frequencies open)

724
00:44:23.327 --> 00:44:25.580
Acting captain 8qu to shuttle bay 2.

725
00:44:25.663 --> 00:44:27.540
Please have the trade ship
we confiscated

726
00:44:27.582 --> 00:44:30.126
during the mudd incident last month
fueled and flight ready.

727
00:44:30.376 --> 00:44:32.378
Captain kirk is en route to you now.

728
00:44:35.756 --> 00:44:37.425
Ready to deploy. captain.

729
00:44:37.550 --> 00:44:39.218
Kirk: Lieutenants. lose the red shirts.

730
00:44:39.594 --> 00:44:41.354
You are k'normian arms dealers.
Put those on.

731
00:44:41.804 --> 00:44:43.198
- Sir?
- Look. if this thing goes south.

732
00:44:43.222 --> 00:44:45.266
there can be nothing
tying us to starfleet.

733
00:44:45.349 --> 00:44:47.852
Unless of course you want to
start a war. Mr. Hendorff.

734
00:44:47.935 --> 00:44:50.271
- No. sir.
- No. sir.

735
00:44:50.396 --> 00:44:51.480
Good. Me. neither.

736
00:45:09.540 --> 00:45:12.251
I am detecting
a single life sign in the ketha province.

737
00:45:12.293 --> 00:45:14.420
Given the information
provided by Mr. Scott.

738
00:45:14.462 --> 00:45:15.822
this is most likely John Harrison.

739
00:45:15.963 --> 00:45:17.506
Mr. Sulu. I think we found our man.

740
00:45:17.632 --> 00:45:18.942
You let him know you mean business.

741
00:45:18.966 --> 00:45:20.134
Sulu: Aye. captain.

742
00:45:20.218 --> 00:45:21.469
(Hailing frequencies opens)

743
00:45:21.969 --> 00:45:23.971
Attention. John Harrison.

744
00:45:24.180 --> 00:45:27.350
This is captain hikaru 8qu
of the u. S. 8. Enterprise.

745
00:45:28.184 --> 00:45:31.896
A shuttle of highly trained officers
is on its way to your location.

746
00:45:32.521 --> 00:45:35.066
If you do not surrender
to them immediately.

747
00:45:35.191 --> 00:45:39.362
I will unleash the entire payload
of advanced long-range torpedoes

748
00:45:39.487 --> 00:45:41.489
currently locked onto your location.

749
00:45:42.114 --> 00:45:45.034
You have two minutes
to confirm your compliance.

750
00:45:45.159 --> 00:45:47.995
Refusal to do so will result
in your obliteration.

751
00:45:50.164 --> 00:45:53.501
If you test me. you will fail.

752
00:45:54.669 --> 00:45:55.920
(Frequencies close)

753
00:45:57.838 --> 00:45:59.340
Mr. Sulu.

754
00:45:59.674 --> 00:46:02.009
remind me never to piss you off.

755
00:46:07.056 --> 00:46:08.776
Spock: We will arrive
at Harrison's location

756
00:46:08.849 --> 00:46:10.184
in three minutes. captain.

757
00:46:10.393 --> 00:46:11.995
It is unlikely that he will come willingly.

758
00:46:12.019 --> 00:46:15.815
I calculate the odds
of him attempting to kill us at 91 .6%.

759
00:46:15.856 --> 00:46:17.024
Fantastic.

760
00:46:17.358 --> 00:46:18.878
Good thing you don't care about dying.

761
00:46:20.653 --> 00:46:22.631
I am sorry. lieutenant.
I could not hear what you said.

762
00:46:22.655 --> 00:46:24.198
I didn't say anything.

763
00:46:26.033 --> 00:46:27.177
Actually. I'd be happy to speak

764
00:46:27.201 --> 00:46:28.303
- if you're willing to listen to me.
- Guys...

765
00:46:28.327 --> 00:46:30.013
Lieutenant. I would prefer
to discuss this in private.

766
00:46:30.037 --> 00:46:31.515
You'd prefer not to discuss this at all.

767
00:46:31.539 --> 00:46:32.557
Spock: Our current circumstances...

768
00:46:32.581 --> 00:46:34.101
Are you really gonna do this right now?

769
00:46:34.125 --> 00:46:35.686
What never seems to require
your undivided focus...

770
00:46:35.710 --> 00:46:37.190
I'm sorry. captain. just two seconds.

771
00:46:37.378 --> 00:46:38.587
- Okay.
- Is us.

772
00:46:38.671 --> 00:46:40.923
At that volcano. you didn't
give a thought to us.

773
00:46:41.215 --> 00:46:43.551
What it would do to me
if you died. Spock.

774
00:46:44.593 --> 00:46:46.554
You didn't feel anything.

775
00:46:47.471 --> 00:46:48.889
You didn't care.

776
00:46:48.931 --> 00:46:51.684
And I'm not the only one who's upset
with you. The captain is. too.

777
00:46:52.226 --> 00:46:54.520
Wha... no. no. no.
Don't drag me into this.

778
00:46:56.105 --> 00:46:57.231
She is right.

779
00:46:57.356 --> 00:47:00.401
Your suggestion that
I do not care about dying is incorrect.

780
00:47:00.568 --> 00:47:02.236
A sentient being's optimal chance

781
00:47:02.361 --> 00:47:04.506
at maximizing their utility
is a long and prosperous life.

782
00:47:04.530 --> 00:47:05.531
Great.

783
00:47:05.740 --> 00:47:07.241
Not exactly a love song. Spock.

784
00:47:07.366 --> 00:47:08.409
You misunderstand.

785
00:47:09.910 --> 00:47:11.954
It is true I chose not to feel anything

786
00:47:12.079 --> 00:47:14.915
upon realizing that
my own life was ending.

787
00:47:16.083 --> 00:47:17.293
As admiral pike was dying.

788
00:47:17.418 --> 00:47:19.253
I joined with his consciousness

789
00:47:19.587 --> 00:47:23.215
and experienced what he felt
at the moment of his passing.

790
00:47:24.091 --> 00:47:26.427
Anger. Confusion.

791
00:47:26.552 --> 00:47:27.928
Loneliness.

792
00:47:28.763 --> 00:47:30.056
Fear

793
00:47:30.556 --> 00:47:33.434
I had experienced those feelings before.

794
00:47:34.101 --> 00:47:35.561
multiplied exponentially

795
00:47:35.603 --> 00:47:38.272
on the day my planet was destroyed.

796
00:47:40.107 --> 00:47:41.776
Such a feeling is something I choose

797
00:47:41.817 --> 00:47:43.944
never to experience again.

798
00:47:46.572 --> 00:47:49.950
Nyota. you mistake my choice not to feel

799
00:47:50.284 --> 00:47:52.787
as a reflection of my not caring.

800
00:47:53.788 --> 00:47:57.458
Well. I assure you.
the truth is precisely the opposite.

801
00:48:01.504 --> 00:48:03.464
- (Disruptors firing)
- (Alarms blaring)

802
00:48:03.631 --> 00:48:04.799
What the hell was that?

803
00:48:05.591 --> 00:48:06.943
What happened? Where's their signal?

804
00:48:06.967 --> 00:48:09.136
It cut out. I'm working to get them back.

805
00:48:12.473 --> 00:48:15.518
We are being pursued by
a d-4 class klingon vessel.

806
00:48:15.726 --> 00:48:16.787
I thought this sector was abandoned!

807
00:48:16.811 --> 00:48:17.978
It must be a random patrol.

808
00:48:18.104 --> 00:48:19.105
Hold on!

809
00:48:23.150 --> 00:48:24.419
This ship has no offensive capabilities.

810
00:48:24.443 --> 00:48:26.320
It's got us. Give me all six fuel cells.

811
00:48:26.362 --> 00:48:28.280
- Spock: Aye. captain.
- (Grunts)

812
00:48:40.251 --> 00:48:41.377
(Alarm blaring)

813
00:48:41.836 --> 00:48:42.837
Damn it!

814
00:48:44.672 --> 00:48:46.841
They're closing fast. bearing 285!

815
00:48:49.510 --> 00:48:51.390
All right. there! There!
We can lose them there.

816
00:48:52.513 --> 00:48:54.433
If you are suggesting
that we utilize the passage

817
00:48:54.473 --> 00:48:55.659
between the approaching structures.

818
00:48:55.683 --> 00:48:57.518
- this ship will not fit.
- We'll fit.

819
00:48:57.685 --> 00:49:00.604
- Captain. we will not fit.
- We'll fit. we'll fit!

820
00:49:02.106 --> 00:49:03.107
(Strains)

821
00:49:10.448 --> 00:49:11.449
(Screams)

822
00:49:14.618 --> 00:49:15.619
(Grunts)

823
00:49:16.704 --> 00:49:18.080
(All breathing heavily)

824
00:49:18.205 --> 00:49:21.083
- I told you we'd fit.
- I am not sure that qualifies.

825
00:49:25.087 --> 00:49:26.213
Any sign of them?

826
00:49:26.380 --> 00:49:27.941
- No. Which worries me.
- Kirk: We lost them!

827
00:49:27.965 --> 00:49:29.192
Or they're jamming our scanners.

828
00:49:29.216 --> 00:49:30.217
Or we lost them.

829
00:49:41.395 --> 00:49:45.483
(Klingon speaking over speakers)

830
00:49:48.360 --> 00:49:50.279
Uhura: They're ordering us to land.

831
00:49:50.446 --> 00:49:52.281
(Klingon continues)

832
00:49:52.698 --> 00:49:54.698
Captain. they're gonna
want to know why we're here.

833
00:49:55.034 --> 00:49:57.036
And they're gonna torture us.

834
00:49:57.161 --> 00:49:58.496
Question us.

835
00:49:58.829 --> 00:50:00.331
And they're gonna kill us.

836
00:50:02.666 --> 00:50:04.418
So we come out shooting.

837
00:50:07.671 --> 00:50:10.591
We're outnumbered. outgunned.

838
00:50:10.883 --> 00:50:13.886
There's no way we survive
if we attack first.

839
00:50:14.929 --> 00:50:17.765
You brought me here
because I speak klingon.

840
00:50:18.432 --> 00:50:20.768
Then let me speak klingon.

841
00:51:08.983 --> 00:51:10.526
Kirk: This isn't going to work.

842
00:51:10.609 --> 00:51:12.653
Spock: It is our only logical option.

843
00:51:12.820 --> 00:51:15.799
And if you interrupt her now. you will
not only incur the wrath of the klingons

844
00:51:15.823 --> 00:51:18.409
but that of lieutenant uhura as well.

845
00:51:30.337 --> 00:51:32.923
(Speaking klingon)

846
00:51:43.350 --> 00:51:45.060
(Breathing heavily)

847
00:51:50.482 --> 00:51:52.151
- Lieutenant.
- Thanks. captain.

848
00:52:23.515 --> 00:52:27.102
(Speaking klingon)

849
00:52:43.410 --> 00:52:44.411
(Whimpers)

850
00:52:56.256 --> 00:52:57.508
(Screams)

851
00:53:18.904 --> 00:53:20.698
(Klingons shouting)

852
00:53:21.198 --> 00:53:23.117
- (Yells)
- (Grunts)

853
00:54:33.020 --> 00:54:35.522
(Weapons fire continues)

854
00:55:01.215 --> 00:55:02.650
- Spock: Stand down.
- How many torpedoes?

855
00:55:02.674 --> 00:55:03.675
- Stand down!
- (Fires)

856
00:55:04.218 --> 00:55:05.219
Harrison: The torpedoes.

857
00:55:05.260 --> 00:55:07.260
the weapons you threatened
me with in your message.

858
00:55:07.387 --> 00:55:08.764
How many are there?

859
00:55:10.682 --> 00:55:11.683
Seventy-two.

860
00:55:18.690 --> 00:55:20.025
I surrender.

861
00:55:31.203 --> 00:55:32.538
(Groaning)

862
00:55:36.917 --> 00:55:38.919
On behalf of Christopher pike.

863
00:55:39.419 --> 00:55:40.504
my friend.

864
00:55:41.171 --> 00:55:42.589
I accept your surrender.

865
00:55:47.052 --> 00:55:49.012
(Grunting)

866
00:55:51.557 --> 00:55:52.975
(Panting)

867
00:55:53.058 --> 00:55:54.059
(Grunts)

868
00:56:07.614 --> 00:56:09.199
Captain!

869
00:56:09.283 --> 00:56:10.284
(Panting)

870
00:56:17.583 --> 00:56:18.917
Captain.

871
00:56:18.959 --> 00:56:20.002
(Thunder rumbles)

872
00:56:30.804 --> 00:56:32.139
Cuff him.

873
00:56:50.908 --> 00:56:51.909
(Communicator chirps)

874
00:56:52.034 --> 00:56:54.328
- Bones. meet me in the brig.
- Bones: Be right there.

875
00:56:54.828 --> 00:56:55.829
Lieutenant.

876
00:56:56.622 --> 00:56:59.791
Contact starfleet. let them know
we have Harrison in custody.

877
00:57:00.334 --> 00:57:02.669
and we'll be on our way once
the warp core is repaired.

878
00:57:02.753 --> 00:57:04.004
Yes. sir.

879
00:57:20.437 --> 00:57:22.677
Bones: Why the hell did he surrender?
Kirk: I don't know.

880
00:57:22.773 --> 00:57:24.667
But he just took out a squad
of klingons single-handedly.

881
00:57:24.691 --> 00:57:25.692
I want to know how.

882
00:57:25.859 --> 00:57:28.028
Sounds like we have
a Superman on board.

883
00:57:28.320 --> 00:57:29.655
Kirk: You tell me.

884
00:57:37.329 --> 00:57:40.082
Put your arm through the hole.
I'm gonna take a blood sample.

885
00:57:50.592 --> 00:57:51.593
(Injection whirs)

886
00:57:54.388 --> 00:57:57.391
Why aren't we moving. captain?

887
00:57:58.725 --> 00:58:01.770
An unexpected malfunction.
perhaps in your warp core

888
00:58:01.937 --> 00:58:04.898
conveniently stranding you
on the edge of klingon space?

889
00:58:04.940 --> 00:58:07.234
- How the hell do you know that?
- Bones.

890
00:58:07.609 --> 00:58:11.405
I think you'd find
my insight valuable. captain.

891
00:58:13.740 --> 00:58:15.659
- We good?
- Yeah.

892
00:58:15.826 --> 00:58:17.327
Let me know what you find.

893
00:58:18.078 --> 00:58:22.416
Ignore me and you
will get everyone on this ship killed.

894
00:58:28.922 --> 00:58:31.482
Spock: Captain. I believe
he will only attempt to manipulate you.

895
00:58:31.675 --> 00:58:33.885
I would not recommend
engaging the prisoner further.

896
00:58:33.927 --> 00:58:35.429
Give me a minute.

897
00:58:47.816 --> 00:58:50.152
Let me explain what's happening here.

898
00:58:50.485 --> 00:58:52.279
You are a criminal.

899
00:58:52.612 --> 00:58:54.948
I watched you murder
innocent men and women.

900
00:58:55.073 --> 00:58:57.617
I was authorized to end you!

901
00:58:57.993 --> 00:59:01.288
And the only reason
why you are still alive

902
00:59:01.413 --> 00:59:02.998
is because I am allowing it.

903
00:59:03.331 --> 00:59:06.001
So shut your mouth.

904
00:59:06.543 --> 00:59:08.962
Oh. captain. are you going
to punch me again

905
00:59:09.004 --> 00:59:11.965
over and over till your arm weakens?

906
00:59:12.007 --> 00:59:14.342
Clearly you want to. so tell me.

907
00:59:15.469 --> 00:59:17.846
why did you allow me to live?

908
00:59:18.263 --> 00:59:19.306
We all make mistakes.

909
00:59:19.473 --> 00:59:22.142
No. I surrendered to you because.

910
00:59:22.184 --> 00:59:24.186
despite your attempt
to convince me othennise.

911
00:59:24.311 --> 00:59:27.189
you seem to have
a conscience. Mr. Kirk.

912
00:59:28.690 --> 00:59:30.859
If you did not.
then it would be impossible for me

913
00:59:30.984 --> 00:59:33.028
to convince you of the truth.

914
00:59:34.029 --> 00:59:38.867
23-17-46-11.

915
00:59:39.951 --> 00:59:42.287
Coordinates not far from earth.

916
00:59:42.370 --> 00:59:45.832
If you want to know why I did what I did.

917
00:59:45.874 --> 00:59:47.167
go and take a look.

918
00:59:47.709 --> 00:59:50.170
Give me one reason
why I should listen to you.

919
00:59:50.337 --> 00:59:52.339
I can give you 72.

920
00:59:52.881 --> 00:59:55.550
And they're on board your ship. captain.

921
00:59:56.510 --> 00:59:59.096
They have been all along.

922
00:59:59.638 --> 01:00:02.349
I suggest you open one up.

923
01:00:04.059 --> 01:00:06.269
(Dance music playing)

924
01:00:12.359 --> 01:00:14.152
(Music playing louder)

925
01:00:18.698 --> 01:00:19.699
_ohl -hi!

926
01:00:27.999 --> 01:00:30.335
You know what really
bothers me. though? (Burps)

927
01:00:30.377 --> 01:00:33.004
It's the modifications.
you know. the enhancements.

928
01:00:33.713 --> 01:00:36.174
Right? And then like that.
I'm off the ship!

929
01:00:36.216 --> 01:00:38.385
Just for trying to do what's right!

930
01:00:39.010 --> 01:00:40.428
And what did you do anyway?

931
01:00:40.554 --> 01:00:41.823
You just stood there like an oyster.

932
01:00:41.847 --> 01:00:43.116
- looking at me!
- (Communicator beeps)

933
01:00:43.140 --> 01:00:44.141
- (Chirps)
- What?

934
01:00:44.432 --> 01:00:45.892
Scotty. it's kirk.

935
01:00:46.059 --> 01:00:47.519
Oh. well now!

936
01:00:47.686 --> 01:00:50.480
If it isn't captain James
tiberius perfect hair!

937
01:00:50.730 --> 01:00:52.667
Did you hear that?
I called him perfect hair. (Laughs)

938
01:00:52.691 --> 01:00:54.067
- Where are you?
- Where are you?

939
01:00:54.192 --> 01:00:55.318
Are you drunk?

940
01:00:55.694 --> 01:00:58.488
What I do in my private time
is my business. jimbo.

941
01:00:58.572 --> 01:01:00.007
I need you to help me out
with something.

942
01:01:00.031 --> 01:01:01.384
Will you take these coordinates down?

943
01:01:01.408 --> 01:01:04.578
23-17-46-11.

944
01:01:05.120 --> 01:01:06.204
Are you writing?

945
01:01:06.246 --> 01:01:08.290
What. you don't think
I can remember four numbers?

946
01:01:08.373 --> 01:01:12.335
(Snickers) Ye of little faith.
What was the third one?

947
01:01:13.044 --> 01:01:14.629
Forty-six.

948
01:01:15.213 --> 01:01:17.591
I don't know exactly
what you're looking for.

949
01:01:18.425 --> 01:01:20.886
but I have a feeling you'll know it
when you see it.

950
01:01:21.595 --> 01:01:23.680
You may have been right
about those torpedoes.

951
01:01:25.599 --> 01:01:27.893
I will consider that an apology.

952
01:01:27.934 --> 01:01:29.644
And I will consider that apology.

953
01:01:31.062 --> 01:01:32.355
You are the one who quit.

954
01:01:32.564 --> 01:01:34.191
You made me quit!

955
01:01:34.524 --> 01:01:36.109
Mr. Scott? (Groans)

956
01:01:36.776 --> 01:01:37.861
Scott.

957
01:01:39.112 --> 01:01:40.906
The nerve of that guy!

958
01:01:42.365 --> 01:01:45.327
I am not doing that man any favors!

959
01:01:47.621 --> 01:01:48.914
All right. then!

960
01:01:49.080 --> 01:01:51.041
Are you out of your corn-fed mind?

961
01:01:51.208 --> 01:01:52.977
You're not actually going
to listen to this guy?

962
01:01:53.001 --> 01:01:54.961
He killed pike. he almost killed you.

963
01:01:55.003 --> 01:01:57.297
and now you think
it's a good idea to pop open a torpedo

964
01:01:57.339 --> 01:01:58.548
because he dared you to.

965
01:01:58.632 --> 01:02:00.467
Why did he save our lives. bones?

966
01:02:00.508 --> 01:02:02.219
The doctor does have a point. captain.

967
01:02:02.302 --> 01:02:04.679
Don't agree with me. Spock.
It makes me very uncomfortable.

968
01:02:04.804 --> 01:02:07.682
Perhaps you. too. should learn
to govern your emotions. doctor.

969
01:02:07.807 --> 01:02:09.118
In this situation. logic dictates...

970
01:02:09.142 --> 01:02:11.186
Logic? Oh. my god! There's a maniac

971
01:02:11.311 --> 01:02:12.997
trying to make us blow up
our own damn ship and...

972
01:02:13.021 --> 01:02:14.832
That's not it.
I don't know why he surrendered.

973
01:02:14.856 --> 01:02:16.316
but that's not it.

974
01:02:16.358 --> 01:02:18.693
Look. we're gonna open a torpedo.
The question is how.

975
01:02:18.818 --> 01:02:20.463
Bones: But. Jim.
without Mr. Scott on board.

976
01:02:20.487 --> 01:02:21.905
who exactly is qualified

977
01:02:21.988 --> 01:02:24.157
to just pop open
a four-ton stick of dynamite?

978
01:02:24.282 --> 01:02:25.968
The admiral's daughter
appeared to have interest

979
01:02:25.992 --> 01:02:27.994
in the torpedoes
and she is a weapons specialist.

980
01:02:28.536 --> 01:02:30.497
Perhaps she could be of some use.

981
01:02:30.705 --> 01:02:32.332
What admiral's daughter?

982
01:02:32.499 --> 01:02:34.876
Carol Marcus. Your new science officer

983
01:02:34.960 --> 01:02:36.670
concealed her identity to board the ship.

984
01:02:37.337 --> 01:02:39.256
When were you going to tell me that?

985
01:02:39.506 --> 01:02:41.549
When it became relevant. As it just did.

986
01:02:41.758 --> 01:02:43.301
Are the torpedoes in the weapons bay?

987
01:02:43.343 --> 01:02:44.903
Loaded and ready to fire.
What are they?

988
01:02:45.178 --> 01:02:46.530
I don't know.
That's why I forged my transfer

989
01:02:46.554 --> 01:02:47.847
onto your ship to find out why.

990
01:02:47.931 --> 01:02:49.683
I do apologize for that.

991
01:02:49.724 --> 01:02:52.519
By the way. if I caused you
any problems. I am sorry.

992
01:02:52.602 --> 01:02:53.895
I'm Carol Marcus.

993
01:02:54.020 --> 01:02:56.022
- James kirk.
- Torpedoes.

994
01:02:57.107 --> 01:02:59.276
My father gave me access
to every program he oversaw.

995
01:02:59.359 --> 01:03:02.028
then I heard he was
developing these prototype torpedoes.

996
01:03:02.070 --> 01:03:05.699
When I went to confront him about it.
he wouldn't even see me.

997
01:03:05.740 --> 01:03:07.867
That's when I discovered
the torpedoes had disappeared

998
01:03:07.951 --> 01:03:10.078
from all official records.

999
01:03:10.412 --> 01:03:12.080
And then he gave them to me.

1000
01:03:12.205 --> 01:03:15.208
You're much cleverer than
your reputation suggests. captain kirk.

1001
01:03:15.417 --> 01:03:16.960
I have a reputation?

1002
01:03:17.043 --> 01:03:18.521
Yes. you do. I'm a friend
of Christine chapel's.

1003
01:03:18.545 --> 01:03:19.629
(Instruments humming)

1004
01:03:19.754 --> 01:03:21.214
Christine. yes. How is she?

1005
01:03:21.256 --> 01:03:23.300
She transferred to the
outer frontier to be a nurse.

1006
01:03:23.383 --> 01:03:24.426
She's much happier now.

1007
01:03:24.551 --> 01:03:25.552
That's good.

1008
01:03:25.760 --> 01:03:28.054
You have no idea
who I'm talking about. do you?

1009
01:03:28.972 --> 01:03:30.012
What are we doing in here?

1010
01:03:30.056 --> 01:03:31.117
Is this shuttle prepped to fly?

1011
01:03:31.141 --> 01:03:32.475
Of course it is.

1012
01:03:32.559 --> 01:03:34.185
- Would you please turn around?
- Why?

1013
01:03:35.103 --> 01:03:36.604
Just turn around.

1014
01:03:37.731 --> 01:03:39.733
It's too dangerous to try and open

1015
01:03:39.774 --> 01:03:41.735
one of these torpedoes
on the enterprise.

1016
01:03:42.068 --> 01:03:44.571
But there is a nearby planetoid.

1017
01:03:44.612 --> 01:03:46.197
I can open one up there.

1018
01:03:46.364 --> 01:03:48.241
But I will need some help.

1019
01:03:48.616 --> 01:03:50.160
Turn around.

1020
01:03:51.244 --> 01:03:52.454
Now!

1021
01:03:53.955 --> 01:03:55.457
Sulu: Captain on the bridge!

1022
01:03:55.749 --> 01:03:57.167
Kirk: Mr. Sulu.

1023
01:03:57.250 --> 01:03:59.753
have doctors Marcus and McCoy
landed on the planetoid yet?

1024
01:03:59.794 --> 01:04:02.464
Sulu: Yes. sir. They're moving the
torpedo into position now.

1025
01:04:02.797 --> 01:04:04.799
Kirk: Good. Any activity
from the klingons?

1026
01:04:04.883 --> 01:04:06.176
Sulu: Not yet.

1027
01:04:06.301 --> 01:04:08.461
But if we're stuck
here much longer. they will find us.

1028
01:04:09.262 --> 01:04:10.982
Lieutenant uhura.
did you let starfleet know

1029
01:04:11.014 --> 01:04:12.599
we have Harrison in custody?

1030
01:04:12.640 --> 01:04:14.559
Yes. sir. No response yet.

1031
01:04:15.643 --> 01:04:17.437
Chekov: Engineering to bridge.

1032
01:04:17.479 --> 01:04:19.606
Hello. Captain. can you hear me?

1033
01:04:19.856 --> 01:04:21.608
Mr. Chekov. give me some good news.

1034
01:04:21.941 --> 01:04:25.153
We found the leak. sir.
but the damage is substantial.

1035
01:04:25.278 --> 01:04:26.279
We're working on it.

1036
01:04:26.446 --> 01:04:28.114
Kirk: Any idea what caused it?

1037
01:04:28.782 --> 01:04:32.327
No. sir. But I accept full responsibility.

1038
01:04:33.828 --> 01:04:37.665
Something tells me
it wasn't your fault. Stay on it.

1039
01:04:37.957 --> 01:04:39.834
Sulu: Shuttle is standing by. captain.

1040
01:04:40.543 --> 01:04:42.295
Bones. thanks for helping out.

1041
01:04:42.379 --> 01:04:44.589
Dr. Marcus asked
for the steadiest hands on the ship.

1042
01:04:44.756 --> 01:04:46.275
You know. when I dreamt
about being stuck

1043
01:04:46.299 --> 01:04:48.301
on a deserted planet
with a gorgeous woman.

1044
01:04:48.385 --> 01:04:49.803
there was no torpedo!

1045
01:04:49.844 --> 01:04:52.514
Kirk: Dr. McCoy. may/remind you.
you are not there to flirt.

1046
01:04:52.639 --> 01:04:55.141
So how can these legendary
hands help you. Dr. Marcus?

1047
01:04:55.266 --> 01:04:56.309
Bones!

1048
01:04:56.393 --> 01:04:58.329
Carol: To understand how
powerful these weapons are.

1049
01:04:58.353 --> 01:04:59.479
we need to open the warhead.

1050
01:04:59.521 --> 01:05:01.207
To do that. we need to
access the fuel compartment.

1051
01:05:01.231 --> 01:05:02.273
Unfortunately for us.

1052
01:05:02.315 --> 01:05:04.901
the warheads on these
weapons are live.

1053
01:05:05.026 --> 01:05:06.087
Sweetheart. I once performed

1054
01:05:06.111 --> 01:05:08.488
an emergency c-section
on a pregnant gorn.

1055
01:05:08.571 --> 01:05:09.572
Octuplets.

1056
01:05:09.656 --> 01:05:11.825
And let me tell you.
those little bastards bite.

1057
01:05:11.991 --> 01:05:14.661
(Groans) I think I can work
some magic on your missile.

1058
01:05:14.702 --> 01:05:17.622
Carol: Dr. McCoy.
there's a bundle of fiber optic cables

1059
01:05:17.664 --> 01:05:19.124
against the inner casing.

1060
01:05:19.165 --> 01:05:21.167
You'll need to cut the 23rd wire down.

1061
01:05:21.209 --> 01:05:22.929
Whatever you do.
do not touch anything else.

1062
01:05:23.002 --> 01:05:24.003
Do you understand?

1063
01:05:24.087 --> 01:05:26.005
Right. The thought
never crossed my mind.

1064
01:05:26.214 --> 01:05:27.340
Carol: Dr. McCoy.

1065
01:05:27.465 --> 01:05:29.426
wait for my word.

1066
01:05:29.551 --> 01:05:31.428
I'm rerouting the detonation processor.

1067
01:05:31.594 --> 01:05:33.596
- Are you ready?
- And raring.

1068
01:05:33.680 --> 01:05:34.681
- Good luck.
- (Yells)

1069
01:05:35.682 --> 01:05:37.517
Sir. the torpedo just armed itself.

1070
01:05:37.600 --> 01:05:39.161
Darwin: The warhead's gonna
detonate in 30 seconds. sir!

1071
01:05:39.185 --> 01:05:41.521
What the hell happened?
I can't get my arm out!

1072
01:05:41.855 --> 01:05:43.416
Target their signal.
Beam them back right now.

1073
01:05:43.440 --> 01:05:47.068
The transporter cannot differentiate
between Dr. McCoy and the torpedo.

1074
01:05:47.193 --> 01:05:48.945
We cannot beam back one
without the other.

1075
01:05:49.028 --> 01:05:50.655
Dr. Marcus. can you disarm it?

1076
01:05:50.697 --> 01:05:52.949
I'm trying. I'm trying.

1077
01:05:53.491 --> 01:05:54.552
Jim. get her the hell out of here!

1078
01:05:54.576 --> 01:05:56.244
No! If you beam me back. he dies!

1079
01:05:56.369 --> 01:05:57.829
Just let me do it!

1080
01:05:58.204 --> 01:05:59.873
Ten. Nine.

1081
01:06:00.039 --> 01:06:01.040
Eight.

1082
01:06:01.249 --> 01:06:03.710
Standing by to transport
Dr. Marcus on your command. sir.

1083
01:06:04.586 --> 01:06:05.587
(Groaning) Four. Three.

1084
01:06:05.837 --> 01:06:06.880
Shit!

1085
01:06:08.047 --> 01:06:10.717
- (Torpedo powers down)
- (Bones groaning)

1086
01:06:11.718 --> 01:06:13.398
- (Sighs)
- Spock: Deactivation successful.

1087
01:06:13.470 --> 01:06:15.013
captain.

1088
01:06:15.054 --> 01:06:16.139
(Radio frequencies open)

1089
01:06:16.222 --> 01:06:17.724
Dr. McCoy. are you all right?

1090
01:06:23.104 --> 01:06:24.397
Bones!

1091
01:06:25.440 --> 01:06:26.608
Jim?

1092
01:06:27.567 --> 01:06:29.736
You're going to want to see this.

1093
01:06:43.750 --> 01:06:44.751
(Instruments beeping)

1094
01:07:35.301 --> 01:07:38.638
Man 1: (On radio) Delta team. deliver
your thrusters to loading clock 12.

1095
01:07:39.514 --> 01:07:41.307
Man 2: U.S.S. Vengeance. bridge crew

1096
01:07:41.349 --> 01:07:43.685
requesting entry to construction hangar.

1097
01:07:46.145 --> 01:07:47.825
Man 1: You are cleared
to enter the hangar.

1098
01:07:56.364 --> 01:07:59.867
Man 3: I need a welding team
on the number one nacelle.

1099
01:08:03.162 --> 01:08:04.664
Holy...

1100
01:08:06.708 --> 01:08:07.709
What have we got?

1101
01:08:07.834 --> 01:08:08.894
Carol: It's quite clever actually.

1102
01:08:08.918 --> 01:08:11.045
This fuel container's been
removed from the torpedo

1103
01:08:11.170 --> 01:08:13.840
and retrofitted to hide this cryo tube.

1104
01:08:15.675 --> 01:08:17.260
- Is he alive?
- Bones: He's alive.

1105
01:08:18.052 --> 01:08:19.512
But if we try to revive him

1106
01:08:19.762 --> 01:08:22.015
without the proper sequencing.
it could kill him.

1107
01:08:22.098 --> 01:08:23.891
This technology's beyond me.

1108
01:08:24.183 --> 01:08:25.518
How advanced. doctor?

1109
01:08:25.727 --> 01:08:28.187
It's not advanced.
That cryo tube is ancient.

1110
01:08:28.855 --> 01:08:31.774
We haven't needed to freeze anyone
since we developed warp capability.

1111
01:08:31.858 --> 01:08:35.194
which explains the most interesting
thing about our friend here.

1112
01:08:36.195 --> 01:08:37.530
He's 300 years old.

1113
01:08:46.372 --> 01:08:48.166
Why is there a man in that torpedo?

1114
01:08:49.083 --> 01:08:50.543
There are men and women

1115
01:08:50.627 --> 01:08:52.420
in all those torpedoes. captain.

1116
01:08:52.503 --> 01:08:54.213
I put them there.

1117
01:08:57.383 --> 01:08:58.509
Who the hell are you?

1118
01:09:02.555 --> 01:09:05.224
A remnant of a time long past.

1119
01:09:06.392 --> 01:09:08.394
Genetically engineered to be superior

1120
01:09:08.436 --> 01:09:11.397
so as to lead others
to peace in a world at war.

1121
01:09:12.565 --> 01:09:17.570
But we were condemned as
criminals. forced into exile.

1122
01:09:18.821 --> 01:09:20.657
For centuries we slept.

1123
01:09:21.741 --> 01:09:25.411
hoping when we awoke.
things would be different.

1124
01:09:25.828 --> 01:09:27.997
But as a result
of the destruction of vulcan.

1125
01:09:28.247 --> 01:09:30.416
your starfleet began
to aggressively search

1126
01:09:30.500 --> 01:09:31.751
distant quadrants of space.

1127
01:09:31.834 --> 01:09:34.587
My ship was found adrift.
I alone was revived.

1128
01:09:34.671 --> 01:09:36.422
Kirk: I looked up "John Harrison."

1129
01:09:36.631 --> 01:09:38.007
Until a year ago. he didn't exist.

1130
01:09:38.091 --> 01:09:41.594
John Harrison was a fiction
created the moment I was awoken

1131
01:09:41.678 --> 01:09:44.931
by your admiral Marcus
to help him advance his cause.

1132
01:09:45.139 --> 01:09:48.601
A smokescreen
to conceal my true identity.

1133
01:09:49.769 --> 01:09:51.813
My name is

1134
01:09:51.938 --> 01:09:53.356
Khan.

1135
01:09:58.277 --> 01:10:00.947
Why would a starfleet admiral

1136
01:10:01.239 --> 01:10:04.784
ask a 300-year-old frozen man for help?

1137
01:10:05.076 --> 01:10:07.620
Because I am better.

1138
01:10:07.954 --> 01:10:10.289
- At what?
- Everything.

1139
01:10:11.791 --> 01:10:13.793
Alexander Marcus needed to respond to

1140
01:10:13.835 --> 01:10:15.962
an uncivilized threat in a civilized time

1141
01:10:16.003 --> 01:10:18.464
and for that he needed a warrior's mind.

1142
01:10:18.506 --> 01:10:19.674
My mind.

1143
01:10:20.007 --> 01:10:22.135
To design weapons and warships.

1144
01:10:22.301 --> 01:10:24.178
Spock: You are suggesting the admiral

1145
01:10:24.345 --> 01:10:26.264
violated every regulation
he vowed to uphold

1146
01:10:26.305 --> 01:10:28.391
simply because he wanted
to exploit your intellect.

1147
01:10:28.599 --> 01:10:30.935
He wanted to exploit my savagery.

1148
01:10:31.060 --> 01:10:33.730
Intellect alone is useless
in a fight. Mr. Spock.

1149
01:10:33.813 --> 01:10:35.606
You... you can't even break a rule.

1150
01:10:35.648 --> 01:10:38.401
How would you be
expected to break bone?

1151
01:10:39.318 --> 01:10:41.946
Marcus used me to design weapons.

1152
01:10:42.155 --> 01:10:44.866
To help him realize
his vision of a militarized starfleet.

1153
01:10:45.032 --> 01:10:47.702
He sent you to use those weapons.

1154
01:10:48.161 --> 01:10:52.165
To fire my torpedoes
on an unsuspecting planet.

1155
01:10:52.832 --> 01:10:55.543
And then he purposely
crippled your ship

1156
01:10:55.752 --> 01:10:59.547
in enemy space.
leading to one inevitable outcome.

1157
01:10:59.672 --> 01:11:01.257
The klingons would come searching

1158
01:11:01.340 --> 01:11:03.176
for whomever was responsible.

1159
01:11:03.259 --> 01:11:05.219
and you would have
no chance of escape.

1160
01:11:05.344 --> 01:11:09.932
Marcus would finally
have the war he talked about.

1161
01:11:10.016 --> 01:11:11.893
The war he always wanted.

1162
01:11:12.185 --> 01:11:13.853
No. No.

1163
01:11:14.854 --> 01:11:15.897
I watched you open fire

1164
01:11:16.022 --> 01:11:18.775
in a room full of
unarmed starfleet officers.

1165
01:11:18.858 --> 01:11:20.693
You killed them in cold blood!

1166
01:11:20.777 --> 01:11:23.196
Marcus took my crew from me.

1167
01:11:23.446 --> 01:11:25.531
You are a murderer!

1168
01:11:25.698 --> 01:11:29.202
He used my friends to control me.

1169
01:11:32.538 --> 01:11:35.208
I tried to smuggle them to safety

1170
01:11:35.291 --> 01:11:37.043
by concealing them in the very weapons

1171
01:11:37.084 --> 01:11:38.795
I had designed.

1172
01:11:40.546 --> 01:11:42.548
but I was discovered.

1173
01:11:43.883 --> 01:11:47.553
I had no choice but to escape alone.

1174
01:11:49.055 --> 01:11:53.226
And when I did.
I had every reason to suspect

1175
01:11:53.309 --> 01:11:57.605
that Marcus had killed every single one

1176
01:11:57.730 --> 01:12:01.108
of the people I hold most dear.

1177
01:12:05.238 --> 01:12:07.907
So I responded in kind.

1178
01:12:11.744 --> 01:12:13.079
My crew

1179
01:12:13.412 --> 01:12:15.998
is my family. kirk.

1180
01:12:16.290 --> 01:12:20.169
Is there anything
you would not do for your family?

1181
01:12:21.796 --> 01:12:23.589
- (Alarm beeps)
- Sulu: Proximity alert. sir!

1182
01:12:23.673 --> 01:12:25.424
There's a ship at warp
heading right for us.

1183
01:12:25.508 --> 01:12:27.468
- Klingons?
- Khan: At warp?

1184
01:12:27.593 --> 01:12:28.928
No. kirk.

1185
01:12:29.011 --> 01:12:31.138
- We both know who it is.
- Sulu: I don't think so.

1186
01:12:31.347 --> 01:12:33.349
It's not coming at us from kronos.

1187
01:12:38.437 --> 01:12:39.748
Lieutenant. move Khan to med bay.

1188
01:12:39.772 --> 01:12:41.083
Post six security officers on him.

1189
01:12:41.107 --> 01:12:42.191
Yes. captain.

1190
01:12:42.483 --> 01:12:44.670
- Sulu: Captain on the bridge!
- (Crew talking indistinctly)

1191
01:12:44.694 --> 01:12:46.195
Kirk: Eta of the incoming ship.

1192
01:12:46.362 --> 01:12:47.613
Three seconds. sir.

1193
01:12:47.655 --> 01:12:49.407
(Alarm blaring)

1194
01:12:49.532 --> 01:12:51.534
- Shields.
- Aye. captain.

1195
01:12:52.702 --> 01:12:54.704
(Talking continues)

1196
01:13:15.850 --> 01:13:16.934
They're hailing us. sir.

1197
01:13:18.311 --> 01:13:19.645
On screen.

1198
01:13:20.688 --> 01:13:22.982
Broadcast shipwide. for the record.

1199
01:13:26.986 --> 01:13:28.321
Captain kirk.

1200
01:13:28.571 --> 01:13:29.655
(Sighs)

1201
01:13:29.780 --> 01:13:32.366
Admiral Marcus. I wasn't expecting you.

1202
01:13:33.367 --> 01:13:35.119
That's a hell of a ship you got there.

1203
01:13:35.328 --> 01:13:36.597
And I wasn't expecting to get word

1204
01:13:36.621 --> 01:13:38.141
that you'd taken Harrison into custody

1205
01:13:38.205 --> 01:13:39.832
in violation of your orders.

1206
01:13:40.833 --> 01:13:42.501
Well. we...

1207
01:13:42.585 --> 01:13:44.545
We had to improvise
when our warp core

1208
01:13:44.670 --> 01:13:46.631
unexpectedly malfunctioned.

1209
01:13:46.672 --> 01:13:48.549
But you already knew that.
didn't you. sir?

1210
01:13:48.716 --> 01:13:50.092
Marcus: / don't take your meaning.

1211
01:13:50.217 --> 01:13:51.777
Well. that's why you're here. isn't it?

1212
01:13:51.844 --> 01:13:53.971
To assist with our repairs?

1213
01:13:54.680 --> 01:13:56.349
Why else would the head of starfleet

1214
01:13:56.432 --> 01:13:58.351
personally come to the edge
of the neutral zone?

1215
01:13:59.769 --> 01:14:01.312
Captain. they're scanning our ship.

1216
01:14:01.562 --> 01:14:03.648
Is there something
I can help you find. sir?

1217
01:14:04.523 --> 01:14:06.192
Where is your prisoner. kirk?

1218
01:14:06.275 --> 01:14:07.515
Kirk: Per starfleet regulation.

1219
01:14:07.568 --> 01:14:11.781
I'm planning on returning Khan
to earth to stand trial.

1220
01:14:12.865 --> 01:14:14.533
Well. shit.

1221
01:14:15.534 --> 01:14:17.036
You talked to him.

1222
01:14:18.245 --> 01:14:20.706
This is exactly what I was
hoping to spare you from.

1223
01:14:21.040 --> 01:14:23.709
I took a tactical risk
and I woke that bastard up.

1224
01:14:23.793 --> 01:14:26.212
believing that his superior intelligence

1225
01:14:26.379 --> 01:14:29.173
could help us protect ourselves
from whatever came at us next.

1226
01:14:31.050 --> 01:14:32.385
But I made a mistake.

1227
01:14:32.885 --> 01:14:36.555
And now the blood
of everybody he's killed is on my hands.

1228
01:14:37.056 --> 01:14:39.058
So I'm asking you.

1229
01:14:39.266 --> 01:14:41.018
give him to me

1230
01:14:41.102 --> 01:14:44.105
so that I can end what I started.

1231
01:14:47.191 --> 01:14:48.901
And what exactly
would you like me to do

1232
01:14:48.943 --> 01:14:50.861
with the rest of his crew. sir?

1233
01:14:52.405 --> 01:14:55.950
Fire them at the klingons?
End 72 lives?

1234
01:14:56.075 --> 01:14:57.535
Start a war in the process?

1235
01:14:57.660 --> 01:15:00.454
He put those people in those torpedoes.

1236
01:15:00.746 --> 01:15:02.266
And I simply didn't want to burden you

1237
01:15:02.331 --> 01:15:04.417
with knowing what was inside of them.

1238
01:15:04.583 --> 01:15:06.419
You saw what this man
can do all by himself.

1239
01:15:06.627 --> 01:15:10.297
Can you imagine what would happen
if we woke up the rest of his crew?

1240
01:15:11.090 --> 01:15:13.467
What else did he tell you?
That he's a peacekeeper?

1241
01:15:13.634 --> 01:15:16.429
He's playing you. son.
don't you see that?

1242
01:15:16.637 --> 01:15:20.141
Khan and his crew were condemned
to death as war criminals.

1243
01:15:20.641 --> 01:15:22.768
And now it is our duty
to carry out that sentence

1244
01:15:22.810 --> 01:15:25.187
before anybody else
dies because of him.

1245
01:15:27.815 --> 01:15:30.151
Now. I'm going to ask you again!

1246
01:15:30.985 --> 01:15:33.112
One last time. son.

1247
01:15:34.989 --> 01:15:36.741
Lower your shields.

1248
01:15:37.158 --> 01:15:38.826
Tell me where he is.

1249
01:15:41.829 --> 01:15:43.789
He's in engineering. sir.

1250
01:15:45.458 --> 01:15:46.834
(Sighs) But I'll have him moved

1251
01:15:46.959 --> 01:15:48.878
to the transporter room right away.

1252
01:15:49.128 --> 01:15:50.921
I'll take it from here.

1253
01:15:51.714 --> 01:15:52.754
Do not drop those shields.

1254
01:15:52.798 --> 01:15:53.817
- Mr. Sulu.
- Sulu: Aye. captain.

1255
01:15:53.841 --> 01:15:54.943
Captain. given your awareness

1256
01:15:54.967 --> 01:15:56.486
of Khan's true location in the med bay.

1257
01:15:56.510 --> 01:15:58.179
may I know the details of your plan?

1258
01:15:58.304 --> 01:16:01.140
I told Marcus we were
bringing a fugitive back to earth.

1259
01:16:01.265 --> 01:16:02.933
That's what we're going to do.

1260
01:16:03.225 --> 01:16:04.745
- (Radio frequencies open)
- Mr. Chekov. can we warp?

1261
01:16:04.769 --> 01:16:06.353
Sir. if we go to warp.

1262
01:16:06.479 --> 01:16:09.607
we run the risk of
seriously damaging the core!

1263
01:16:09.648 --> 01:16:11.448
- Kirk: Can we do it?
- (Sighs in frustration)

1264
01:16:11.817 --> 01:16:15.571
Technically. yes. but I
would not advise it. captain.

1265
01:16:15.821 --> 01:16:17.073
-Noted. _(Frequencies close)

1266
01:16:17.823 --> 01:16:19.992
Mr. Sulu. set course for earth.

1267
01:16:20.117 --> 01:16:21.160
Yes. sir.

1268
01:16:22.328 --> 01:16:23.662
Punch it.

1269
01:16:30.669 --> 01:16:33.506
Well. at least we're moving again.

1270
01:16:33.672 --> 01:16:34.965
(Beeping)

1271
01:16:35.341 --> 01:16:39.011
If you think you're safe
at warp. you're wrong.

1272
01:16:42.890 --> 01:16:44.517
Lieutenant uhura. contact starfleet.

1273
01:16:44.558 --> 01:16:46.161
Tell them we were pursued
into the neutral zone

1274
01:16:46.185 --> 01:16:47.812
by an unmarked federation ship.

1275
01:16:47.853 --> 01:16:48.938
Comms are down. sir.

1276
01:16:51.482 --> 01:16:52.626
Permission to come on the bridge.

1277
01:16:52.650 --> 01:16:53.692
Kirk: Dr. Marcus.

1278
01:16:54.360 --> 01:16:55.796
He's gonna catch up with us.
and when he does.

1279
01:16:55.820 --> 01:16:57.214
the only thing
that's gonna stop him destroying

1280
01:16:57.238 --> 01:16:58.715
this ship is me.
so you have to let me talk to him.

1281
01:16:58.739 --> 01:17:00.619
Carol. we're at warp.
He can't catch up with us.

1282
01:17:00.658 --> 01:17:02.010
Yes. he can.
He's been developing a ship

1283
01:17:02.034 --> 01:17:03.345
that has advanced warp capabilities...

1284
01:17:03.369 --> 01:17:05.996
Captain! I'm getting
a reading I don't understand.

1285
01:17:13.587 --> 01:17:14.880
(Crew grunting)

1286
01:17:19.718 --> 01:17:21.053
(People screaming)

1287
01:17:35.860 --> 01:17:38.237
- Where are we?
- We're 237.000 kilometers from earth.

1288
01:17:38.279 --> 01:17:39.381
- Kirk: Damage report!
- Weapons are way down.

1289
01:17:39.405 --> 01:17:40.841
- Sulu: Shields are dropping.
- We're defenseless. sir.

1290
01:17:40.865 --> 01:17:42.105
Sir. we have a bulkhead breach.

1291
01:17:42.241 --> 01:17:44.219
- Where's the damage?
- Major hull damage. captain.

1292
01:17:44.243 --> 01:17:45.452
(Firing continues)

1293
01:17:47.413 --> 01:17:48.455
(Screaming)

1294
01:17:48.622 --> 01:17:49.623
(Grunting)

1295
01:17:49.748 --> 01:17:52.126
Evasive maneuvers! Get us to earth!
Right now!

1296
01:17:52.209 --> 01:17:55.504
Captain! Stop!
Everybody on this ship is going to die

1297
01:17:55.588 --> 01:17:56.857
if you don't let me speak to him.

1298
01:17:56.881 --> 01:17:58.465
(Alarms blaring)

1299
01:17:59.300 --> 01:18:01.093
Uhura. hail him.

1300
01:18:01.760 --> 01:18:04.096
Sir. It's me. It's Carol.

1301
01:18:06.432 --> 01:18:07.933
(Firing stops)

1302
01:18:13.731 --> 01:18:16.358
What are you doing on that ship?

1303
01:18:16.567 --> 01:18:18.235
I heard what you said.

1304
01:18:19.904 --> 01:18:21.071
That you made a mistake

1305
01:18:21.155 --> 01:18:23.574
and now you're doing
everything you can to fix it.

1306
01:18:24.742 --> 01:18:26.076
But. dad.

1307
01:18:29.455 --> 01:18:33.167
(stammering) I don't believe that
the man who raised me

1308
01:18:33.250 --> 01:18:37.880
is capable of destroying a ship
full of innocent people.

1309
01:18:38.130 --> 01:18:40.841
And. if I'm wrong about that.

1310
01:18:41.008 --> 01:18:43.469
then you're gonna have to
do it with me on board.

1311
01:18:46.430 --> 01:18:48.098
Actually. Carol. I won't.

1312
01:18:53.103 --> 01:18:54.623
- Jim...
- Can we intercept the transport signal?

1313
01:18:54.647 --> 01:18:55.648
No. sir.

1314
01:18:57.983 --> 01:18:58.984
- (Screams)
- Carol!

1315
01:18:59.610 --> 01:19:01.487
Captain kirk. without authorization

1316
01:19:01.570 --> 01:19:03.697
and in league with
the fugitive John Harrison.

1317
01:19:03.781 --> 01:19:05.658
you went rogue in enemy territory.

1318
01:19:05.741 --> 01:19:06.784
leaving me no choice

1319
01:19:06.867 --> 01:19:08.786
but to hunt you down and destroy you.

1320
01:19:09.119 --> 01:19:11.372
- Lock phasers.
- Wait. sir. wait. wait. wait!

1321
01:19:11.538 --> 01:19:12.539
I'll make this quick.

1322
01:19:12.623 --> 01:19:14.917
Target all aft torpedoes
on the enterprise bridge.

1323
01:19:15.125 --> 01:19:17.461
Sir. my crew
was just following my orders.

1324
01:19:17.544 --> 01:19:20.089
I take full responsibility for my actions.

1325
01:19:20.172 --> 01:19:22.216
But they were mine
and they were mine alone.

1326
01:19:23.217 --> 01:19:25.177
If I transmit Khan's location to you now.

1327
01:19:25.344 --> 01:19:27.680
all that I ask is that you spare them.

1328
01:19:34.561 --> 01:19:36.397
Please. sir.

1329
01:19:38.232 --> 01:19:40.401
I'll do anything you want.

1330
01:19:41.819 --> 01:19:43.654
Just let them live.

1331
01:19:45.155 --> 01:19:47.574
That's a hell of an apology.

1332
01:19:47.825 --> 01:19:49.910
But if it's any consolation.

1333
01:19:49.994 --> 01:19:51.912
I was never going to spare your crew.

1334
01:19:54.081 --> 01:19:55.416
Fire when...

1335
01:20:15.853 --> 01:20:16.937
I'm sorry.

1336
01:20:17.146 --> 01:20:18.439
(Gasps)

1337
01:20:22.609 --> 01:20:23.610
(Powering down)

1338
01:20:24.361 --> 01:20:25.529
Our weapons won't fire. sir!

1339
01:20:25.612 --> 01:20:26.923
Our shields are down!
We're losing power!

1340
01:20:26.947 --> 01:20:29.199
Someone in engineering
just manually reset our systems!

1341
01:20:29.450 --> 01:20:31.744
What do you mean. "someone"?
(Shouts) Who?

1342
01:20:31.827 --> 01:20:34.455
Their weapons have powered down. Sir.

1343
01:20:34.538 --> 01:20:36.832
Scotty: (On radio)
Enterprise! Can you hear me?

1344
01:20:36.915 --> 01:20:38.000
Scotty!

1345
01:20:40.127 --> 01:20:42.087
Guess what I found behind Jupiter.

1346
01:20:42.254 --> 01:20:44.089
- You're on that ship!
- / snuck on.

1347
01:20:44.256 --> 01:20:45.692
And seeing as I've just
committed an act of treason

1348
01:20:45.716 --> 01:20:47.360
against a starfleet
admiral. I'd really like

1349
01:20:47.384 --> 01:20:49.553
to get off this bloody ship.
Now beam me out!

1350
01:20:49.720 --> 01:20:50.804
You're a miracle worker.

1351
01:20:50.888 --> 01:20:52.723
We're a little low on power right now.

1352
01:20:52.848 --> 01:20:53.891
Just stand by. Stand by.

1353
01:20:53.932 --> 01:20:55.243
What do you mean. "low on power"?

1354
01:20:55.267 --> 01:20:56.547
What happened to the enterprise?

1355
01:20:57.186 --> 01:20:58.506
- (Doors opening)
- Call you back.

1356
01:21:00.230 --> 01:21:01.398
Scotty!

1357
01:21:02.608 --> 01:21:05.069
Spock. Our ship. how is she?

1358
01:21:05.486 --> 01:21:06.945
Our options are limited. captain.

1359
01:21:07.029 --> 01:21:08.989
We cannot fire and we cannot flee.

1360
01:21:12.159 --> 01:21:13.327
There is one option.

1361
01:21:13.535 --> 01:21:15.287
Uhura. when you get Scotty back.

1362
01:21:15.371 --> 01:21:17.164
- patch him through.
- Yes. sir.

1363
01:21:17.373 --> 01:21:18.540
Mr. Spock. you have the conn.

1364
01:21:22.753 --> 01:21:24.630
Captain. I strongly object.

1365
01:21:24.671 --> 01:21:26.507
To what? I haven't said anything yet.

1366
01:21:26.590 --> 01:21:28.234
Since we cannot take
the ship from the outside.

1367
01:21:28.258 --> 01:21:29.819
the only way we can take it
is from within.

1368
01:21:29.843 --> 01:21:31.529
And as a large boarding party
would be detected.

1369
01:21:31.553 --> 01:21:32.655
it is optimal for you to take

1370
01:21:32.679 --> 01:21:34.431
as few members
of the crew as possible.

1371
01:21:34.515 --> 01:21:36.975
You will meet resistance.
requiring personnel

1372
01:21:37.142 --> 01:21:38.244
with advanced combat abilities

1373
01:21:38.268 --> 01:21:40.104
and innate knowledge of that ship.

1374
01:21:40.354 --> 01:21:42.398
This indicates that
you plan to align with Khan.

1375
01:21:42.481 --> 01:21:44.358
the very man
we were sent here to destroy.

1376
01:21:44.608 --> 01:21:46.294
Kirk: I'm not aligning with him.
I'm using him.

1377
01:21:46.318 --> 01:21:48.278
"The enemy of my enemy is my friend."

1378
01:21:48.362 --> 01:21:50.406
An arabic proverb attributed
to a prince who was

1379
01:21:50.489 --> 01:21:52.249
betrayed and decapitated
by his own subjects.

1380
01:21:52.282 --> 01:21:54.451
Still. it's a hell of a quote.

1381
01:21:54.535 --> 01:21:56.846
- I will go with you. captain.
- No. I need you on the bridge.

1382
01:21:56.870 --> 01:21:58.664
I cannot allow you to do this.

1383
01:21:58.705 --> 01:22:00.558
It is my function aboard
this ship to advise you

1384
01:22:00.582 --> 01:22:02.060
on making the wisest
decisions possible.

1385
01:22:02.084 --> 01:22:03.168
something I firmly believe

1386
01:22:03.252 --> 01:22:04.854
you are incapable
of doing in this moment.

1387
01:22:04.878 --> 01:22:06.213
You're right!

1388
01:22:07.631 --> 01:22:09.484
What I'm about to do.
it doesn't make any sense.

1389
01:22:09.508 --> 01:22:11.969
it's not logical. It is a gut feeling.

1390
01:22:15.389 --> 01:22:17.975
I have no idea what I'm supposed to do.

1391
01:22:19.143 --> 01:22:21.311
I only know what I can do.

1392
01:22:21.979 --> 01:22:23.498
The enterprise and her crew
need someone

1393
01:22:23.522 --> 01:22:26.316
in that chair that knows what he's doing.

1394
01:22:29.987 --> 01:22:31.405
And it's not me.

1395
01:22:34.324 --> 01:22:35.659
It's you. Spock.

1396
01:22:47.713 --> 01:22:50.382
(Medical crew
speaking indistinctly)

1397
01:22:58.474 --> 01:23:00.194
Tell me everything you know
about that ship.

1398
01:23:00.559 --> 01:23:02.311
Dreadnought class.

1399
01:23:02.394 --> 01:23:04.062
Two times the size.
three times the speed.

1400
01:23:04.146 --> 01:23:07.024
Advanced weaponry.
Modified for a minimal crew.

1401
01:23:07.065 --> 01:23:09.985
Unlike most federation vessels.
it's built solely for combat.

1402
01:23:11.153 --> 01:23:13.405
I will do everything I can

1403
01:23:14.072 --> 01:23:16.366
to make you answer for what you did.

1404
01:23:22.581 --> 01:23:24.082
But right now I need your help.

1405
01:23:24.333 --> 01:23:26.251
In exchange for what?

1406
01:23:27.586 --> 01:23:29.922
You said you'd do anything
for your crew.

1407
01:23:31.423 --> 01:23:34.176
- I can guarantee their safety.
- Captain.

1408
01:23:35.093 --> 01:23:38.764
You can't even guarantee
the safety of your own crew.

1409
01:23:44.770 --> 01:23:46.490
Bones. what are you doing
with that tribble?

1410
01:23:47.356 --> 01:23:48.690
The tribble's dead.

1411
01:23:48.774 --> 01:23:52.110
I'm injecting Khan's platelets into
the deceased tissue of a necrotic host.

1412
01:23:52.194 --> 01:23:53.195
(Injection whirs)

1413
01:23:53.278 --> 01:23:55.739
Khan's cells regenerate
like nothing I've ever seen.

1414
01:23:55.822 --> 01:23:57.574
and I want to know why.

1415
01:24:02.704 --> 01:24:04.957
You coming with me or not?

1416
01:24:07.543 --> 01:24:09.211
You want to do what?

1417
01:24:09.378 --> 01:24:10.772
We're coming over there.
Sulu's maneuvering

1418
01:24:10.796 --> 01:24:12.631
the enterprise
into position as we speak.

1419
01:24:12.714 --> 01:24:14.174
To this ship? How?

1420
01:24:14.424 --> 01:24:16.802
There's a cargo door.
hangar 7. access port 101a.

1421
01:24:16.885 --> 01:24:19.030
You need to find
the manual override to open that airlock.

1422
01:24:19.054 --> 01:24:21.974
Are you crazy? Whoever you are.

1423
01:24:22.140 --> 01:24:24.077
Just listen to him. Scotty.
It's gonna be all right.

1424
01:24:24.101 --> 01:24:25.477
It is not gonna be all right.

1425
01:24:25.561 --> 01:24:27.354
You want me to open
an airlock into space.

1426
01:24:27.437 --> 01:24:30.315
whereupon I will freeze.
die and explode!

1427
01:24:30.566 --> 01:24:32.085
Lieutenant.
from our current position. is it possible

1428
01:24:32.109 --> 01:24:34.069
to establish contact with new vulcan?

1429
01:24:34.736 --> 01:24:37.239
- I'll do my best.
- Thank you.

1430
01:24:38.991 --> 01:24:41.326
Mr. Sulu. what is
the status of the other ship?

1431
01:24:41.410 --> 01:24:42.995
Their systems are still offline.

1432
01:24:43.078 --> 01:24:44.913
I'm aligning our ship now.

1433
01:25:19.364 --> 01:25:20.644
Scotty. how we doing over there?

1434
01:25:21.033 --> 01:25:23.035
Scotty: Captain.
I wish I had better news.

1435
01:25:23.619 --> 01:25:25.787
They've locked out access
to the ship's computer.

1436
01:25:25.871 --> 01:25:27.456
They'll have full weapons in

1437
01:25:27.831 --> 01:25:29.041
three minutes.

1438
01:25:29.082 --> 01:25:30.768
That means next time
I won't be able to stop them

1439
01:25:30.792 --> 01:25:32.628
destroying the enterprise. Stand by.

1440
01:25:34.379 --> 01:25:35.440
Commander. our trash exhaust
is aimed at

1441
01:25:35.464 --> 01:25:37.716
access port 101a of the other ship.

1442
01:25:37.799 --> 01:25:39.551
Captain. the ships are aligned.

1443
01:25:39.676 --> 01:25:40.677
Copy that.

1444
01:25:40.719 --> 01:25:43.847
- Scotty!
- I'm in the hangar. Give me a minute.

1445
01:25:44.431 --> 01:25:46.224
(Panting)

1446
01:25:48.143 --> 01:25:50.479
I'm running. Stand by.

1447
01:25:53.065 --> 01:25:55.567
(Panting and groaning)

1448
01:26:00.322 --> 01:26:01.823
Whoa. whoa. hold on. now. captain.

1449
01:26:01.907 --> 01:26:04.826
This door is very wee.
I mean. you know. small.

1450
01:26:05.035 --> 01:26:07.037
It's four square meters. tops.

1451
01:26:07.204 --> 01:26:09.122
It's gonna be like
jumping out of a moving car.

1452
01:26:09.206 --> 01:26:11.124
off a bridge. into your shot glass.

1453
01:26:11.333 --> 01:26:13.085
It's okay. I've done it before.

1454
01:26:15.003 --> 01:26:16.088
Yeah. it was vertical.

1455
01:26:16.171 --> 01:26:19.091
We jumped onto a... it was a...
(Muttering)

1456
01:26:19.174 --> 01:26:20.384
It doesn't matter. Scotty...

1457
01:26:20.425 --> 01:26:21.694
Did you find the manual override?

1458
01:26:21.718 --> 01:26:23.011
The manual override. Scotty.

1459
01:26:23.261 --> 01:26:24.930
Not yet. not yet.

1460
01:26:26.765 --> 01:26:28.016
(Panel beeping)

1461
01:26:31.520 --> 01:26:33.247
Captain. before you launch.
you should be aware there is

1462
01:26:33.271 --> 01:26:35.071
a considerable debris field
between our ships.

1463
01:26:35.273 --> 01:26:37.859
- Spock. not now. Scotty. you good?
- It's not easy!

1464
01:26:37.943 --> 01:26:40.696
Just give me two seconds.
all right. you mad bastard!

1465
01:26:48.870 --> 01:26:51.206
Tell me this is gonna work.

1466
01:26:52.040 --> 01:26:53.458
I have neither the information

1467
01:26:53.542 --> 01:26:55.377
nor the confidence to do so. doctor.

1468
01:26:55.544 --> 01:26:56.878
Scotty: Okay. captain. stand by.

1469
01:26:57.212 --> 01:26:58.630
Boy. you're a real comfort.

1470
01:27:00.048 --> 01:27:02.050
- Come on. come on. come on.
- (Beeping)

1471
01:27:02.175 --> 01:27:03.218
Yes!

1472
01:27:03.343 --> 01:27:04.928
Okay. okay! I'm set to open the door.

1473
01:27:04.970 --> 01:27:06.138
You ready?

1474
01:27:06.304 --> 01:27:07.639
Are you?

1475
01:27:10.892 --> 01:27:12.227
Kirk: Spock. pull the trigger.

1476
01:27:13.478 --> 01:27:14.479
Yes. captain.

1477
01:27:20.235 --> 01:27:21.903
Launching activation sequence on

1478
01:27:22.154 --> 01:27:23.488
three.

1479
01:27:23.613 --> 01:27:24.781
two.

1480
01:27:25.490 --> 01:27:26.491
one.

1481
01:27:36.752 --> 01:27:39.337
Sir. kirk is headed for collision at .432!

1482
01:27:39.671 --> 01:27:41.423
Captain. there is debris directly ahead.

1483
01:27:41.506 --> 01:27:42.507
Copy that.

1484
01:27:46.511 --> 01:27:47.929
Whoa! Jim. you're way off course!

1485
01:27:48.096 --> 01:27:49.336
I know. I know! I can see that.

1486
01:27:59.816 --> 01:28:01.336
- (Phaser humming)
- Guard: Don't move.

1487
01:28:03.612 --> 01:28:05.113
Use your display compass. captain.

1488
01:28:05.197 --> 01:28:06.239
You must correct precisely

1489
01:28:06.323 --> 01:28:08.408
- 37.243 degrees.
- Kirk: Got it.

1490
01:28:08.700 --> 01:28:09.701
I'm working my way back.

1491
01:28:12.537 --> 01:28:14.577
Scotty. you're gonna be ready
with that door. right?

1492
01:28:15.749 --> 01:28:17.083
What are you doing in here?

1493
01:28:17.542 --> 01:28:21.213
Wee bit of maintenance
on the airlock console. You're big.

1494
01:28:21.338 --> 01:28:22.672
Mr. Scott. where are you?

1495
01:28:22.714 --> 01:28:24.114
Captain. he can't seem to hear you.

1496
01:28:24.174 --> 01:28:25.693
I'm working on getting
his signal back. Stand by.

1497
01:28:25.717 --> 01:28:26.802
(Glass cracks)

1498
01:28:28.804 --> 01:28:30.639
- Damn it.
- Spock: Captain. what is it?

1499
01:28:30.722 --> 01:28:31.723
My helmet was hit.

1500
01:28:31.807 --> 01:28:33.391
Uhura. tell me you have Mr. Scott back.

1501
01:28:33.642 --> 01:28:35.119
Not yet. I'm still working on a signal.

1502
01:28:35.143 --> 01:28:36.603
His communicator is working.

1503
01:28:36.728 --> 01:28:38.888
- I don't know why he isn't responding.
- What is that?

1504
01:28:38.939 --> 01:28:40.458
Are you starfleet or private security?

1505
01:28:40.482 --> 01:28:41.483
Show me your other hand.

1506
01:28:41.566 --> 01:28:42.710
Because you look like private security.

1507
01:28:42.734 --> 01:28:44.194
Ensign: Imminent collision detected!

1508
01:28:44.361 --> 01:28:45.403
Khan. use evasive action!

1509
01:28:45.445 --> 01:28:47.531
- There is debris directly ahead.
- I see it.

1510
01:28:54.579 --> 01:28:55.890
- (Beeping)
- Mr. Sulu. did we lose Khan?

1511
01:28:55.914 --> 01:28:56.974
I don't know. commander.
I'm having trouble

1512
01:28:56.998 --> 01:28:58.333
tracking him in all this debris.

1513
01:28:59.167 --> 01:29:00.418
Was Khan hit?

1514
01:29:00.502 --> 01:29:01.753
We are trying to find him now.

1515
01:29:02.087 --> 01:29:03.731
Captain. you need to adjust
your target destination

1516
01:29:03.755 --> 01:29:06.091
to 183 by 473 degrees.

1517
01:29:13.932 --> 01:29:15.350
(Glass cracking)

1518
01:29:17.435 --> 01:29:19.521
Spock. my display's dead.
I'm flying blind.

1519
01:29:20.105 --> 01:29:21.773
Captain. without your display compass.

1520
01:29:21.857 --> 01:29:24.001
hitting your target destination
is mathematically impossible.

1521
01:29:24.025 --> 01:29:25.235
Spock. if I get back.

1522
01:29:25.277 --> 01:29:27.197
we really need to talk
about your bedside manner.

1523
01:29:27.279 --> 01:29:29.281
Commander. he's not going to make it.

1524
01:29:30.365 --> 01:29:31.616
(Beeps)

1525
01:29:34.828 --> 01:29:36.454
My display is still functioning.

1526
01:29:36.538 --> 01:29:38.266
I see you. kirk.
you're 200 meters ahead of me

1527
01:29:38.290 --> 01:29:39.499
at my one o'clock.

1528
01:29:39.583 --> 01:29:41.626
Come to your left
a few degrees and follow me.

1529
01:29:54.264 --> 01:29:55.783
Scotty. we're getting close.
We need a warm welcome.

1530
01:29:55.807 --> 01:29:58.268
Do you copy? Do you copy? Scotty?

1531
01:29:58.310 --> 01:29:59.644
If you can hear us. Mr. Scott.

1532
01:29:59.728 --> 01:30:01.521
- open the door in ten. nine...
- Scotty!

1533
01:30:01.646 --> 01:30:02.665
That person counting down.

1534
01:30:02.689 --> 01:30:03.729
- what is that?
- Eight...

1535
01:30:03.773 --> 01:30:04.959
Scotty: I think
you're hearing things. mate.

1536
01:30:04.983 --> 01:30:06.818
- A_seven_.
- Mr. Scott. where are you?

1537
01:30:06.860 --> 01:30:09.946
- Spock: Six. five...
- 1.800 meters. 1.600 meters.

1538
01:30:10.113 --> 01:30:11.507
- Scotty. where are you?
- Three...

1539
01:30:11.531 --> 01:30:13.325
- Do you copy. Scotty? Please!
- Two...

1540
01:30:13.450 --> 01:30:14.677
- Sorry about this.
- About what?

1541
01:30:14.701 --> 01:30:16.012
- Mr. Scott. open the door!
- Open the door!

1542
01:30:16.036 --> 01:30:17.621
- Spock: Mr. Scott. now!
- (Gasps)

1543
01:30:17.704 --> 01:30:19.331
(Guard screaming)

1544
01:30:25.211 --> 01:30:26.338
- (Yelling)
- (Grunts)

1545
01:30:26.922 --> 01:30:28.340
(Gasps)

1546
01:30:28.381 --> 01:30:30.425
(Grunting)

1547
01:30:37.098 --> 01:30:38.433
(Panting)

1548
01:30:38.850 --> 01:30:40.477
Welcome aboard.

1549
01:30:41.019 --> 01:30:42.062
(Panting)

1550
01:30:42.187 --> 01:30:44.397
- It's good to see you. Scotty.
- Who is that?

1551
01:30:45.106 --> 01:30:46.358
(Groaning)

1552
01:30:46.858 --> 01:30:48.526
Khan. Scotty. Scotty. Khan.

1553
01:30:48.777 --> 01:30:49.945
Hello.

1554
01:30:50.695 --> 01:30:52.072
They'll know we're here.

1555
01:30:52.155 --> 01:30:54.115
I know the best way to the bridge.

1556
01:30:57.953 --> 01:30:59.621
It's locked to stun.

1557
01:30:59.871 --> 01:31:01.206
Theirs won't be.

1558
01:31:01.456 --> 01:31:03.124
Try not to get shot.

1559
01:31:04.209 --> 01:31:05.543
(Phasers humming)

1560
01:31:06.211 --> 01:31:09.047
Commander. I have that
transmission as requested.

1561
01:31:09.381 --> 01:31:11.049
On screen. please.

1562
01:31:11.383 --> 01:31:12.550
Uhura: Stand by.

1563
01:31:18.723 --> 01:31:20.058
Mr. Spock.

1564
01:31:21.559 --> 01:31:22.894
Mr. Spock.

1565
01:31:27.399 --> 01:31:28.650
Guard: Admiral.

1566
01:31:31.611 --> 01:31:32.737
I'll deal with you in a...

1567
01:31:35.407 --> 01:31:37.742
I am ashamed to be your daughter.

1568
01:31:40.578 --> 01:31:41.579
(Door opens)

1569
01:31:41.663 --> 01:31:44.332
Sir. we just had
a hangar door open on deck 13.

1570
01:31:45.750 --> 01:31:46.918
Khan.

1571
01:31:47.168 --> 01:31:49.480
Scotty: They're going to have
full power and we're walking?

1572
01:31:49.504 --> 01:31:50.731
The turbolifts are easily tracked

1573
01:31:50.755 --> 01:31:52.173
and Marcus would have us in a cage.

1574
01:31:52.257 --> 01:31:54.509
This path runs adjacent
to the engine room.

1575
01:31:54.592 --> 01:31:56.320
They know they
won't be able to use their weapons here

1576
01:31:56.344 --> 01:31:57.655
without destabilizing the warp core.

1577
01:31:57.679 --> 01:31:59.097
which gives us the advantage.

1578
01:31:59.180 --> 01:32:01.933
- Where'd you find this guy?
- It's a long story.

1579
01:32:02.183 --> 01:32:03.268
Spock: / will be brief.

1580
01:32:04.269 --> 01:32:07.605
In your travels. did you ever
encounter a man named Khan?

1581
01:32:12.193 --> 01:32:13.278
As you know.

1582
01:32:13.361 --> 01:32:15.697
I have made a vow
never to give you information

1583
01:32:15.780 --> 01:32:18.700
that could potentially alter your destiny.

1584
01:32:19.617 --> 01:32:24.289
Your path is yours to walk.
and yours alone.

1585
01:32:27.959 --> 01:32:29.961
That being said.

1586
01:32:31.129 --> 01:32:35.300
Khan noonien Singh is
the most dangerous adversary

1587
01:32:35.383 --> 01:32:37.635
the enterprise ever faced.

1588
01:32:38.303 --> 01:32:41.181
He is brilliant. ruthless.

1589
01:32:41.389 --> 01:32:43.933
and he will not hesitate to kill

1590
01:32:43.975 --> 01:32:45.935
every single one of you.

1591
01:32:49.647 --> 01:32:51.483
Did you defeat him?

1592
01:32:52.317 --> 01:32:55.653
At great cost. Yes.

1593
01:32:57.655 --> 01:32:58.656
How?

1594
01:32:58.782 --> 01:33:00.885
I don't mean to tempt fate here.
but where is everybody?

1595
01:33:00.909 --> 01:33:02.678
The ship is designed
to be flown by minimal crew.

1596
01:33:02.702 --> 01:33:03.745
one. if necessary.

1597
01:33:03.828 --> 01:33:05.080
- One? I...
- (Grunting)

1598
01:33:14.923 --> 01:33:16.007
(Groaning)

1599
01:33:24.891 --> 01:33:25.892
(Groans)

1600
01:33:26.351 --> 01:33:28.686
- You all right?
- Yeah. Where's Khan?

1601
01:33:34.192 --> 01:33:36.528
Lieutenant. I need you to
assemble all senior medical

1602
01:33:36.611 --> 01:33:38.211
and engineering staff
in the weapons bay.

1603
01:33:38.947 --> 01:33:40.115
All right.

1604
01:33:41.616 --> 01:33:44.786
Dr. McCoy. you inadvertently
activated a torpedo.

1605
01:33:44.869 --> 01:33:46.149
Could you replicate the process?

1606
01:33:46.204 --> 01:33:47.681
Why the hell would I want to do that?

1607
01:33:47.705 --> 01:33:49.124
Can you or can you not?

1608
01:33:49.207 --> 01:33:51.960
Damn it. man. I'm a doctor.
not a torpedo technician!

1609
01:33:52.168 --> 01:33:53.395
The fact that you
are a doctor is precisely

1610
01:33:53.419 --> 01:33:55.046
why I need you to listen very carefully.

1611
01:33:56.548 --> 01:33:57.882
Where is he?

1612
01:34:03.388 --> 01:34:04.722
Shit!

1613
01:34:05.056 --> 01:34:07.016
Khan: This way.

1614
01:34:09.227 --> 01:34:11.813
The minute we get
to the bridge. drop him.

1615
01:34:11.896 --> 01:34:15.233
What. stun him? Khan?
I thought he was helping us.

1616
01:34:15.483 --> 01:34:17.235
I'm pretty sure we're helping him.

1617
01:34:22.657 --> 01:34:24.117
(Doors opening)

1618
01:34:26.494 --> 01:34:27.829
Power coming online. sir!

1619
01:34:27.996 --> 01:34:29.247
Retarget the enterprise now.

1620
01:34:29.372 --> 01:34:30.474
- Crewman: Aye. sir.
- (Phasers firing)

1621
01:34:30.498 --> 01:34:32.000
(Men grunting)

1622
01:34:44.470 --> 01:34:45.805
Make sure he stays down.

1623
01:34:46.890 --> 01:34:48.224
- Excuse me.
- Yeah.

1624
01:34:52.020 --> 01:34:54.355
Admiral Marcus. you're under arrest.

1625
01:34:54.522 --> 01:34:56.322
You're not actually
going to do this. are you?

1626
01:34:57.859 --> 01:35:00.111
Admiral. get out of the chair.

1627
01:35:00.278 --> 01:35:02.780
You better stop
and think about what you're doing. kirk.

1628
01:35:02.947 --> 01:35:04.949
You better think about
what you did on kronos.

1629
01:35:05.158 --> 01:35:07.660
You made an incursion
onto an enemy planet!

1630
01:35:08.036 --> 01:35:09.954
You killed a klingon patrol.

1631
01:35:10.121 --> 01:35:13.291
Even if you got away without
a trace. war is coming.

1632
01:35:13.541 --> 01:35:16.878
And who is going to lead us? You?

1633
01:35:17.212 --> 01:35:18.755
If I'm not in charge.

1634
01:35:18.838 --> 01:35:21.549
our entire way of life is decimated!

1635
01:35:22.217 --> 01:35:24.719
So you want me off this ship.

1636
01:35:25.053 --> 01:35:27.388
you better kill me.

1637
01:35:27.555 --> 01:35:29.307
I'm not going to kill you. sir.

1638
01:35:30.475 --> 01:35:34.145
But I could stun your ass
and drag you out of that chair.

1639
01:35:34.395 --> 01:35:37.065
I'd rather not do that
in front of your daughter.

1640
01:35:40.818 --> 01:35:42.820
- You all right?
- Yes. captain.

1641
01:35:45.365 --> 01:35:46.407
- (Grunts)
- Jim!

1642
01:35:46.491 --> 01:35:47.492
(Grunts)

1643
01:35:49.535 --> 01:35:51.162
- (Groans)
- (Yells)

1644
01:35:59.671 --> 01:36:01.422
Listen! Wait!

1645
01:36:01.714 --> 01:36:02.715
(Grunts)

1646
01:36:03.258 --> 01:36:04.592
- (Bone cracks)
- (Screams)

1647
01:36:08.179 --> 01:36:09.764
(Marcus groaning)

1648
01:36:13.184 --> 01:36:14.185
- You...
- (Screaming)

1649
01:36:14.686 --> 01:36:18.064
You should have let me sleep.

1650
01:36:19.190 --> 01:36:20.334
- (Marcus screaming)
- (Skull cracking)

1651
01:36:20.358 --> 01:36:22.360
(Screaming)

1652
01:36:23.361 --> 01:36:24.601
Where is the captain. Mr. Sulu?

1653
01:36:24.696 --> 01:36:27.031
Our sensor array's down. sir.
I can't find him.

1654
01:36:27.073 --> 01:36:28.074
(Kirk grunts)

1655
01:36:28.783 --> 01:36:30.827
I'm going to make this
very simple for you.

1656
01:36:30.952 --> 01:36:33.538
- Captain.
- Your crew for my crew.

1657
01:36:33.705 --> 01:36:34.872
You betrayed us.

1658
01:36:35.373 --> 01:36:37.166
You are smart. Mr. Spock.

1659
01:36:37.208 --> 01:36:38.626
Spock don't... (Groans)

1660
01:36:41.045 --> 01:36:44.215
Mr. Spock. give me my crew.

1661
01:36:45.049 --> 01:36:46.634
And what will you do
when you get them?

1662
01:36:46.759 --> 01:36:49.220
Continue the work we were doing
before we were banished.

1663
01:36:49.345 --> 01:36:51.198
Which. as I understand it.
involves the mass genocide

1664
01:36:51.222 --> 01:36:54.225
of any being you find to be
less than superior.

1665
01:36:54.392 --> 01:36:56.394
Shall I destroy you. Mr. Spock?

1666
01:36:56.728 --> 01:36:59.397
Or will you give me what I want?

1667
01:37:01.983 --> 01:37:03.818
We have no transporter capabilities.

1668
01:37:03.943 --> 01:37:05.862
Fortunately mine are
perfectly functional.

1669
01:37:05.987 --> 01:37:08.156
Drop your shields.

1670
01:37:08.573 --> 01:37:10.199
If I do so. I have no guarantee

1671
01:37:10.283 --> 01:37:11.993
that you will not destroy the enterprise.

1672
01:37:12.076 --> 01:37:14.579
Well. let's play this out
logically then. Mr. Spock.

1673
01:37:14.662 --> 01:37:16.372
Firstly. I will kill your captain

1674
01:37:16.414 --> 01:37:18.082
to demonstrate my resolve.

1675
01:37:18.124 --> 01:37:21.044
Then if yours holds.
I will have no choice

1676
01:37:21.085 --> 01:37:23.629
but to kill you and your entire crew.

1677
01:37:23.796 --> 01:37:25.465
If you destroy our ship.

1678
01:37:25.548 --> 01:37:27.550
you will also destroy your own people.

1679
01:37:27.675 --> 01:37:30.553
Your crew requires oxygen
to survive. mine does not.

1680
01:37:30.595 --> 01:37:32.263
I will target your life support systems

1681
01:37:32.347 --> 01:37:34.515
located behind the aft nacelle.

1682
01:37:34.724 --> 01:37:37.935
And after every single person
aboard your ship suffocates.

1683
01:37:38.061 --> 01:37:42.565
I will walk over your cold
corpses to recover my people.

1684
01:37:45.109 --> 01:37:46.527
Now.

1685
01:37:47.278 --> 01:37:49.280
shall we begin?

1686
01:37:53.284 --> 01:37:54.619
Lower shields.

1687
01:37:56.162 --> 01:37:57.789
- (Beeping)
- (Shields power down)

1688
01:37:58.539 --> 01:38:00.500
A wise choice. Mr. Spock.

1689
01:38:00.666 --> 01:38:02.001
(Grunts)

1690
01:38:02.210 --> 01:38:04.337
- (Gasps)
- (Coughing)

1691
01:38:06.672 --> 01:38:08.132
(Panel beeping)

1692
01:38:08.466 --> 01:38:11.219
Khan: I see your 72 torpedoes
are still in their tubes.

1693
01:38:11.636 --> 01:38:13.971
If they are not mine.
commander. I will know it.

1694
01:38:14.222 --> 01:38:16.391
Vulcans do not lie.

1695
01:38:17.308 --> 01:38:19.477
The torpedoes are yours.

1696
01:38:19.727 --> 01:38:21.229
(Beeping)

1697
01:38:30.279 --> 01:38:31.948
Thank you. Mr. Spock.

1698
01:38:32.281 --> 01:38:34.450
I have fulfilled your terms.

1699
01:38:34.951 --> 01:38:36.202
Now fulfill mine.

1700
01:38:37.370 --> 01:38:39.330
Khan: Well. kirk.

1701
01:38:39.539 --> 01:38:41.707
it seems apt to return you to your crew.

1702
01:38:41.833 --> 01:38:43.960
- (Groaning)
- After all.

1703
01:38:46.963 --> 01:38:50.258
no ship should go down
without her captain.

1704
01:38:50.383 --> 01:38:52.009
(Alarms blaring)

1705
01:38:52.885 --> 01:38:54.345
He's locking phasers on us. sir!

1706
01:39:00.560 --> 01:39:02.562
- Let us out of here now!
- (Explosion)

1707
01:39:08.943 --> 01:39:10.403
(All grunting)

1708
01:39:10.903 --> 01:39:12.530
- (Crew clamoring)
- Shields at 6%!

1709
01:39:12.738 --> 01:39:14.699
The torpedoes!
How much time. lieutenant?

1710
01:39:14.824 --> 01:39:15.825
Twelve seconds. sir!

1711
01:39:15.950 --> 01:39:17.034
Crew of the enterprise.

1712
01:39:17.076 --> 01:39:18.716
prepare for imminent
proximity detonation.

1713
01:39:18.995 --> 01:39:20.830
What's he talking about?
What detonation?

1714
01:39:20.913 --> 01:39:22.999
The torpedoes.
He armed the damn torpedoes!

1715
01:39:23.207 --> 01:39:24.625
(Powering up)

1716
01:39:30.381 --> 01:39:31.382
(Grunting)

1717
01:39:41.517 --> 01:39:43.117
Sir. their weapons
have been knocked out.

1718
01:39:44.187 --> 01:39:46.272
- Not bad. commander.
- Thank you. lieutenant.

1719
01:39:46.647 --> 01:39:48.566
- Bones!
- Bones!

1720
01:39:48.608 --> 01:39:50.735
- Bones: Nurse!
- I got you. I got you.

1721
01:39:50.818 --> 01:39:52.945
- Dr. Marcus.
- (Groaning)

1722
01:39:54.530 --> 01:39:55.615
Good to see you. Jim.

1723
01:39:55.698 --> 01:39:57.338
You helped Spock
detonate those torpedoes?

1724
01:39:57.366 --> 01:39:58.409
Damn right I did.

1725
01:39:58.451 --> 01:39:59.952
He killed Khan's crew!

1726
01:40:00.036 --> 01:40:01.621
Spock's cold. but he's not that cold.

1727
01:40:02.038 --> 01:40:04.081
I've got Khan's crew.

1728
01:40:04.207 --> 01:40:06.375
Seventy-two human popsicles

1729
01:40:06.584 --> 01:40:09.086
safe and sound in their cryo tubes.

1730
01:40:09.879 --> 01:40:11.439
- Son of a bitch!
- (Ship powering down)

1731
01:40:16.761 --> 01:40:18.641
Crewman: Sir. the central
power grid is failing!

1732
01:40:18.763 --> 01:40:21.933
- Switch to auxiliary power.
- Auxiliary power failing. sir.

1733
01:40:29.565 --> 01:40:31.685
Sulu: Commander. our ship's
caught in earth's gravity!

1734
01:40:31.817 --> 01:40:33.903
- Can we stop?
- I can't do anything.

1735
01:40:38.533 --> 01:40:39.951
(Screaming)

1736
01:40:43.162 --> 01:40:44.914
Sorry! Oh. no.

1737
01:40:45.164 --> 01:40:46.290
Clear the area!

1738
01:40:46.999 --> 01:40:49.961
Engage emergency lockdown!
I hope you don't get seasick.

1739
01:40:50.086 --> 01:40:51.963
- Do you?
- Yeah.

1740
01:40:52.171 --> 01:40:53.771
Lieutenant. sound evacuation. all decks.

1741
01:40:53.798 --> 01:40:54.799
Aye. sir.

1742
01:40:55.967 --> 01:40:59.637
As acting captain.
I order you to abandon this ship.

1743
01:41:00.930 --> 01:41:02.848
I will remain behind and divert all power

1744
01:41:03.015 --> 01:41:04.493
to life support
and evacuation shuttle bays.

1745
01:41:04.517 --> 01:41:06.245
Automated female voice:
Evacuation protocols...

1746
01:41:06.269 --> 01:41:08.771
I order you to abandon the ship!

1747
01:41:08.896 --> 01:41:11.983
All due respect. commander.
but we're not going anywhere.

1748
01:41:12.275 --> 01:41:13.943
Attention all decks.

1749
01:41:13.985 --> 01:41:15.861
Evacuation protocols initiated.

1750
01:41:16.028 --> 01:41:19.156
One day I've been off this ship!
One bloody day!

1751
01:41:20.533 --> 01:41:21.993
(Screaming)

1752
01:41:23.160 --> 01:41:25.413
Gravity systems are failing.
Hold on! Hold on!

1753
01:41:25.496 --> 01:41:26.664
(Grunting)

1754
01:41:27.832 --> 01:41:29.000
(Crew screaming)

1755
01:41:29.083 --> 01:41:30.811
Automated female voice:
Attention. all decks.

1756
01:41:30.835 --> 01:41:32.336
Evacuation protocols initiated.

1757
01:41:32.378 --> 01:41:34.463
- (Woman screaming)
- Proceed to exit bays

1758
01:41:34.505 --> 01:41:36.441
- and report to your assigned shuttle.
- (Panting)

1759
01:41:36.465 --> 01:41:37.818
Scotty: There won't be time
for evacuation

1760
01:41:37.842 --> 01:41:41.012
if we don't get power
to stabilize the damn ship!

1761
01:41:41.178 --> 01:41:43.681
- Can we restore it?
- Only from engineering.

1762
01:41:43.848 --> 01:41:46.350
We have to get back to the warp core.

1763
01:41:46.517 --> 01:41:49.061
- Attention all decks.
- (Crew screaming)

1764
01:41:49.186 --> 01:41:50.521
Jim?

1765
01:41:51.480 --> 01:41:53.858
Kirk: Scotty. we got to get
the power back on! Come on!

1766
01:41:58.404 --> 01:41:59.905
(Both panting)

1767
01:42:11.667 --> 01:42:13.002
- Scotty. we got to jump!
- What?

1768
01:42:13.252 --> 01:42:14.503
Jump! Jump!

1769
01:42:14.629 --> 01:42:16.297
- Oh. god.
- (Both grunting)

1770
01:42:17.048 --> 01:42:19.508
Emergency power at 15% and dropping.

1771
01:42:19.634 --> 01:42:21.069
Automated female voice:
Attention. all decks.

1772
01:42:21.093 --> 01:42:23.554
Evacuation protocols initiated.

1773
01:42:23.638 --> 01:42:27.141
Proceed to exit bays
and report to your assigned shuttle.

1774
01:42:29.226 --> 01:42:30.728
(Both yelling)

1775
01:42:32.730 --> 01:42:34.482
(Straining and grunting)

1776
01:42:37.151 --> 01:42:38.569
(Screaming)

1777
01:42:39.654 --> 01:42:41.197
- Jim?
- Hold on!

1778
01:42:41.405 --> 01:42:42.740
I can't.

1779
01:42:51.082 --> 01:42:52.083
(Straining)

1780
01:42:53.000 --> 01:42:54.502
(Grunting)

1781
01:42:57.880 --> 01:42:58.923
(Gasping)

1782
01:42:59.757 --> 01:43:01.092
- (Grunting)
- (Laughs)

1783
01:43:01.300 --> 01:43:02.802
I've got you. captain!

1784
01:43:02.968 --> 01:43:04.637
- Chekov.
- Don't let go!

1785
01:43:05.137 --> 01:43:06.514
(Straining)

1786
01:43:15.773 --> 01:43:18.543
Even if we get the warp core online.
we've still got to redirect the power!

1787
01:43:18.567 --> 01:43:20.253
- He's right. captain!
- What are you talking about?

1788
01:43:20.277 --> 01:43:22.363
Someone has to hit
the manual override.

1789
01:43:22.446 --> 01:43:23.656
Laddie. there's a switch...

1790
01:43:23.739 --> 01:43:26.033
Behind the deflector dish!
I'll flip the switch!

1791
01:43:26.117 --> 01:43:27.493
Let's go!

1792
01:43:28.953 --> 01:43:30.287
(Grunting)

1793
01:43:30.454 --> 01:43:31.455
Oh. no.

1794
01:43:31.831 --> 01:43:33.290
(Whimpering)

1795
01:43:35.710 --> 01:43:37.962
Oy-yoy! Oy-yoy! Oy-yoy-yoy!

1796
01:43:38.129 --> 01:43:39.630
(Screaming)

1797
01:43:42.800 --> 01:43:45.594
Evacuation protocols initiated.

1798
01:43:45.636 --> 01:43:48.305
Proceed to exit bays
and report to your assigned shuttle.

1799
01:43:48.389 --> 01:43:50.057
(All screaming)

1800
01:43:50.224 --> 01:43:52.160
Mr. Sulu. divert
any remaining power to stabilizers.

1801
01:43:52.184 --> 01:43:54.019
Doing what I can. sir. Doing what I can.

1802
01:43:54.186 --> 01:43:55.479
(Panting)

1803
01:43:57.982 --> 01:43:59.316
(Grunting)

1804
01:44:00.359 --> 01:44:01.652
(Beeping)

1805
01:44:02.486 --> 01:44:03.487
(Straining)

1806
01:44:07.032 --> 01:44:08.492
(Powering up)

1807
01:44:10.411 --> 01:44:13.414
Automated female voice:
Core misaligned. Danger.

1808
01:44:13.497 --> 01:44:15.166
- Oh. no. no. no. no!
- What?

1809
01:44:15.249 --> 01:44:16.500
The housings are misaligned!

1810
01:44:16.584 --> 01:44:18.502
There's no way
we can redirect the power!

1811
01:44:18.586 --> 01:44:21.589
The ship's dead. sir. She's gone.

1812
01:44:23.007 --> 01:44:24.925
- No. she's not.
- Wait. Jim!

1813
01:44:25.050 --> 01:44:27.553
If we go in there. we'll die!

1814
01:44:27.636 --> 01:44:29.680
Do you hear me?
The radiation will kill us!

1815
01:44:29.930 --> 01:44:32.183
Will you listen to me?
What the hell are you doing?

1816
01:44:32.266 --> 01:44:33.493
I'm opening the door. I'm going in.

1817
01:44:33.517 --> 01:44:35.728
That door is there to stop us
from getting irradiated!

1818
01:44:35.811 --> 01:44:38.105
We'd be dead
before we made the climb!

1819
01:44:40.524 --> 01:44:41.817
You're not making the climb.

1820
01:44:41.901 --> 01:44:42.902
(Grunts)

1821
01:44:43.027 --> 01:44:45.738
Automated female voice:
Danger. Core misaligned.

1822
01:44:45.821 --> 01:44:48.616
Danger. Core misaligned.

1823
01:44:55.414 --> 01:44:56.749
(Grunting)

1824
01:45:15.226 --> 01:45:17.102
(Electricity crackling)

1825
01:45:47.758 --> 01:45:49.718
If we don't get power
or shields back online.

1826
01:45:49.802 --> 01:45:52.429
we're gonna be incinerated on re-entry!

1827
01:45:57.142 --> 01:45:58.394
(Grunts)

1828
01:46:27.172 --> 01:46:28.173
(Grunts)

1829
01:46:38.392 --> 01:46:39.685
(Yells)

1830
01:46:56.410 --> 01:46:57.828
(Screams)

1831
01:46:59.163 --> 01:47:00.247
Warp core is back online!

1832
01:47:00.456 --> 01:47:01.957
Spock: Maximum thrusters. Mr. Sulu!

1833
01:47:07.087 --> 01:47:09.381
Thrusters at maximum!
Stand by! Stand by!

1834
01:47:20.559 --> 01:47:22.603
(Engines engaging)

1835
01:47:34.865 --> 01:47:36.617
(Chuckles softly)

1836
01:47:36.867 --> 01:47:38.994
- Shields restored!
- Commander. power online.

1837
01:47:39.286 --> 01:47:41.288
Mr. Spock. altitude stabilizing.

1838
01:47:41.622 --> 01:47:43.457
It's a miracle.

1839
01:47:45.209 --> 01:47:47.211
There are no such things.

1840
01:47:47.544 --> 01:47:48.921
(Communicator beeping)

1841
01:47:49.630 --> 01:47:51.048
Scotty: Engineering to bridge.

1842
01:47:51.131 --> 01:47:52.383
- Mr. Spock!
- Mr. Scott.

1843
01:47:52.466 --> 01:47:55.386
Sir. you'd better get down here.

1844
01:47:55.469 --> 01:47:56.804
Better hurry.

1845
01:48:19.493 --> 01:48:20.577
Open it.

1846
01:48:20.744 --> 01:48:22.464
The decontamination process
is not complete.

1847
01:48:22.579 --> 01:48:23.807
You'd flood the whole compartment.

1848
01:48:23.831 --> 01:48:25.874
The door's locked. sir.

1849
01:48:30.629 --> 01:48:31.964
(Groaning)

1850
01:48:34.174 --> 01:48:35.175
(Groans)

1851
01:48:35.342 --> 01:48:37.052
(Breathing heavily)

1852
01:48:38.679 --> 01:48:40.764
(Mechanism whirring)

1853
01:48:55.362 --> 01:48:56.447
How's our ship?

1854
01:48:58.198 --> 01:48:59.700
Out of danger.

1855
01:49:02.202 --> 01:49:04.455
You saved the crew.

1856
01:49:05.873 --> 01:49:08.709
You used what he wanted against him.

1857
01:49:12.713 --> 01:49:14.506
That's a nice move.

1858
01:49:16.216 --> 01:49:18.218
It is what you would have done.

1859
01:49:19.970 --> 01:49:21.221
And this.

1860
01:49:22.890 --> 01:49:24.892
this is what you would have done.

1861
01:49:25.225 --> 01:49:27.394
It was only logical.

1862
01:49:33.734 --> 01:49:35.444
I'm scared. Spock.

1863
01:49:39.156 --> 01:49:40.908
Help me not be.

1864
01:49:45.329 --> 01:49:47.664
How do you choose not to feel?

1865
01:49:54.421 --> 01:49:56.090
I do not know.

1866
01:49:58.759 --> 01:50:00.844
Right now I am failing.

1867
01:50:07.518 --> 01:50:10.604
I want you to know
why I couldn't let you die.

1868
01:50:14.775 --> 01:50:16.527
Why I went back for you.

1869
01:50:18.445 --> 01:50:20.864
Because you are my friend.

1870
01:50:56.733 --> 01:50:57.734
(Coughs)

1871
01:51:44.281 --> 01:51:47.284
(Yelling) Khan!

1872
01:51:49.870 --> 01:51:51.205
God. that was close!

1873
01:51:54.541 --> 01:51:58.754
Set destination. starfleet headquarters!

1874
01:51:58.921 --> 01:52:00.231
Automated male voice:
Engines compromised.

1875
01:52:00.255 --> 01:52:02.299
Cannot guarantee destination.

1876
01:52:02.382 --> 01:52:03.800
Confirm order.

1877
01:52:04.134 --> 01:52:05.385
Confirm.

1878
01:52:05.510 --> 01:52:07.137
(Rumbling)

1879
01:52:07.638 --> 01:52:09.640
(Concerned murmuring)

1880
01:52:14.019 --> 01:52:15.771
(Crowd exclaiming in shock)

1881
01:52:19.358 --> 01:52:20.484
(Clamoring)

1882
01:52:44.174 --> 01:52:45.759
(All screaming)

1883
01:53:09.783 --> 01:53:12.035
Search the enemy ship for signs of life.

1884
01:53:12.286 --> 01:53:14.204
Sir. there's no way anyone survived.

1885
01:53:15.497 --> 01:53:16.623
He could.

1886
01:53:17.374 --> 01:53:18.458
Yes. sir.

1887
01:53:18.917 --> 01:53:20.961
(Sirens wailing)

1888
01:53:30.345 --> 01:53:31.555
(Grunts)

1889
01:53:32.556 --> 01:53:34.057
(Alarms blaring)

1890
01:53:47.154 --> 01:53:48.155
(Grunts)

1891
01:53:50.240 --> 01:53:51.825
Whoa! Hejustjumped 30 meters!

1892
01:53:51.992 --> 01:53:53.160
Can we beam him up?

1893
01:53:53.243 --> 01:53:54.345
Chekov: There's too much damage.

1894
01:53:54.369 --> 01:53:55.746
I have no incoming signal.

1895
01:53:55.912 --> 01:53:58.749
But it may be possible
to beam you down. sir.

1896
01:53:59.207 --> 01:54:00.417
Go get him.

1897
01:54:05.589 --> 01:54:08.175
- Stand by for coordinates.
- Yes. sir.

1898
01:54:08.508 --> 01:54:11.011
Enter 3517 by 2598.

1899
01:54:11.136 --> 01:54:12.929
Coordinates confirmed.

1900
01:54:17.517 --> 01:54:19.186
(People clamoring)

1901
01:55:34.553 --> 01:55:35.762
(Sighs)

1902
01:55:38.682 --> 01:55:40.725
(Tribble chittering softly)

1903
01:55:45.772 --> 01:55:47.482
(Equipment beeping)

1904
01:55:51.069 --> 01:55:52.904
Get me a cryo tube. now!

1905
01:56:20.474 --> 01:56:21.641
(Grunting)

1906
01:56:38.742 --> 01:56:40.410
(Yelling in pain)

1907
01:56:47.792 --> 01:56:48.793
(Injection whirs)

1908
01:56:48.919 --> 01:56:50.295
Get this guy out of the cryo tube.

1909
01:56:50.378 --> 01:56:51.713
Keep him in an induced coma.

1910
01:56:51.755 --> 01:56:53.256
We're gonna put kirk inside.

1911
01:56:53.298 --> 01:56:55.067
It's our only chance to
preserve his brain function.

1912
01:56:55.091 --> 01:56:56.927
How much of Khan's blood is left?

1913
01:56:57.052 --> 01:56:58.053
None.

1914
01:56:58.929 --> 01:57:01.973
Enterprise to Spock. Spock!

1915
01:57:03.934 --> 01:57:04.935
(Grunts)

1916
01:57:43.014 --> 01:57:44.641
(Straining)

1917
01:58:02.867 --> 01:58:05.036
Activate the cryogenic sequence.

1918
01:58:05.120 --> 01:58:06.955
- (Beeping)
- (Hissing)

1919
01:58:07.038 --> 01:58:08.498
McCoy to bridge.

1920
01:58:09.165 --> 01:58:11.585
I can't reach Spock. I need Khan alive.

1921
01:58:11.668 --> 01:58:14.838
You get that son of a bitch
back on board right now!

1922
01:58:15.714 --> 01:58:17.299
I think he can save kirk.

1923
01:58:17.424 --> 01:58:18.693
Can we beam them up to the ship?

1924
01:58:18.717 --> 01:58:21.177
They keep moving! I can't
get a lock on either of them.

1925
01:58:21.219 --> 01:58:22.554
Can you beam someone down?

1926
01:58:29.769 --> 01:58:31.479
(Both straining)

1927
01:58:33.815 --> 01:58:35.191
(Yelling)

1928
01:58:57.505 --> 01:58:58.548
- (Screams)
- Spock!

1929
01:59:06.097 --> 01:59:07.098
Spock!

1930
01:59:07.390 --> 01:59:09.225
Spock. stop! Stop!

1931
01:59:09.809 --> 01:59:12.020
He's our only chance to save kirk!

1932
01:59:21.738 --> 01:59:24.074
George: What is it?
Winona: It's a boy.

1933
01:59:24.407 --> 01:59:25.487
George: Let's call him Jim.

1934
01:59:25.533 --> 01:59:27.869
Pike: Your father was
captain of a starship for 12 minutes.

1935
01:59:27.911 --> 01:59:31.831
He saved 800 lives.
I dare you to do better.

1936
01:59:32.082 --> 01:59:33.416
(Gasps)

1937
01:59:41.007 --> 01:59:44.010
Don't be so melodramatic.
You were barely dead.

1938
01:59:44.094 --> 01:59:46.554
It was the transfusion
that really took its toll.

1939
01:59:46.888 --> 01:59:47.907
You were out cold for two weeks.

1940
01:59:47.931 --> 01:59:48.932
Transfusion?

1941
01:59:49.057 --> 01:59:51.768
Your cells were heavily irradiated.
We had no choice.

1942
01:59:52.560 --> 01:59:53.770
Khan?

1943
01:59:53.895 --> 01:59:55.063
Once we caught him.

1944
01:59:55.188 --> 01:59:57.816
I synthesized a serum
from his superblood.

1945
01:59:57.899 --> 02:00:00.443
Tell me. are you feeling homicidal?

1946
02:00:00.568 --> 02:00:02.112
Power mad? Despotic?

1947
02:00:02.278 --> 02:00:03.947
No more than usual.

1948
02:00:04.406 --> 02:00:05.573
How'd you catch him?

1949
02:00:05.949 --> 02:00:07.283
I didn't.

1950
02:00:16.126 --> 02:00:17.752
You saved my life.

1951
02:00:17.961 --> 02:00:20.463
Uhura and I had
something to do with it. too. you know.

1952
02:00:22.006 --> 02:00:24.300
You saved my life. captain.
And the lives...

1953
02:00:24.759 --> 02:00:26.094
Spock. just...

1954
02:00:27.804 --> 02:00:29.139
Thank you.

1955
02:00:30.473 --> 02:00:32.642
You are welcome. Jim.

1956
02:00:43.445 --> 02:00:46.823
Kirk: There will always be
those who mean to do us harm.

1957
02:00:48.783 --> 02:00:50.160
To stop them.

1958
02:00:50.785 --> 02:00:54.664
we risk awakening
the same evil within ourselves.

1959
02:01:00.670 --> 02:01:03.298
Our first instinct is to seek revenge

1960
02:01:03.339 --> 02:01:05.675
when those we love are taken from us.

1961
02:01:08.762 --> 02:01:10.513
But that's not who we are.

1962
02:01:12.056 --> 02:01:13.683
We are here today

1963
02:01:13.850 --> 02:01:16.686
to rechristen the USS. Enterprise.

1964
02:01:16.853 --> 02:01:19.689
and to honor those who lost their lives

1965
02:01:20.690 --> 02:01:22.317
nearly one year ago.

1966
02:01:22.817 --> 02:01:24.986
When Christopher pike
first gave me his ship

1967
02:01:25.028 --> 02:01:27.489
he had me recite the captain's oath.

1968
02:01:28.364 --> 02:01:31.201
words I didn't appreciate at the time.

1969
02:01:31.868 --> 02:01:34.913
Now I see them as a call
for us to remember

1970
02:01:35.747 --> 02:01:37.582
who we once were.

1971
02:01:39.501 --> 02:01:41.878
and who we must be again.

1972
02:01:43.171 --> 02:01:44.672
And those words?

1973
02:01:45.340 --> 02:01:48.384
Space. the final frontier.

1974
02:01:48.843 --> 02:01:52.555
These are the voyages
of the starship enterprise.

1975
02:01:53.389 --> 02:01:55.266
Her five-year mission.

1976
02:01:55.350 --> 02:01:57.227
to explore strange new worlds.

1977
02:01:57.894 --> 02:02:01.397
to seek out new life
and new civilizations.

1978
02:02:02.065 --> 02:02:05.860
to boldly go
where no one has gone before.

1979
02:02:08.863 --> 02:02:10.740
Chekov: Captain on the bridge.

1980
02:02:13.868 --> 02:02:16.246
It's hard to get out of it
once you've had a taste.

1981
02:02:16.287 --> 02:02:17.789
isn't that right. Mr. Sulu?

1982
02:02:17.872 --> 02:02:20.208
"Captain" does have a nice ring to it.

1983
02:02:20.250 --> 02:02:21.709
Chair's all yours. sir.

1984
02:02:23.545 --> 02:02:25.046
Mr. Scott.

1985
02:02:25.213 --> 02:02:26.214
How's our core?

1986
02:02:26.256 --> 02:02:27.924
Purring like a kitten. captain.

1987
02:02:27.966 --> 02:02:30.260
She's ready for a long journey.

1988
02:02:30.343 --> 02:02:31.511
Excellent.

1989
02:02:31.636 --> 02:02:34.138
Come on. bones! It's gonna be fun.

1990
02:02:35.390 --> 02:02:38.643
Five years in space. God help me.

1991
02:02:38.935 --> 02:02:40.311
Dr. Marcus.

1992
02:02:41.729 --> 02:02:43.565
I'm glad you could be
a part of the family.

1993
02:02:44.023 --> 02:02:45.733
It's nice to have a family.

1994
02:02:48.111 --> 02:02:49.195
Kirk: Spock.

1995
02:02:49.445 --> 02:02:50.613
Captain.

1996
02:02:53.575 --> 02:02:55.076
Where shall we go?

1997
02:02:56.411 --> 02:02:59.581
As a mission of this duration
has never been attempted.

1998
02:03:01.583 --> 02:03:04.085
I defer to your good judgment. captain.

1999
02:03:13.094 --> 02:03:15.638
Mr. Sulu. take us out.

2000
02:03:15.763 --> 02:03:17.265
Aye. captain.

2000
02:03:18.305 --> 02:04:18.556
